title: no bake chocolate cheesecake
directions: In small microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips. Microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.
Set aside to cool.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and butter until creamy; on low speed of electric mixer, blend in melted chocolate.
Fold in whipped topping until blended; spoon into crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cover; refrigerate leftover cheesecake.
Garnish as desired.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and beat at low speed for 3 minutes.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into a floured and greased pan.
Bake at temperature on box.
Let cool 25 minutes before removing.

title: sunbeams (rolls)
directions: Soften the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water to which 1 tablespoon of sugar has been added.
Combine rest of sugar, milk, shortening and salt in large mixer bowl.
Using slow speed, add eggs.
Turn mixer a bit slower (no. 1) and add 2 cups flour and yeast.
Turn beaters to medium speed (no. 5) and beat for about 4 minutes. With a spoon, add as much of flour as can be stirred in without kneading.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until double in bulk.
(Put in warm place for this.)
Turn out on lightly floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Fold over as for Parker House rolls.
Bake at 425° until lightly browned, 15 minutes.

title: polenta-italian "pasta" dish
directions: Melt butter.
Add water, cornmeal and salt.
Cook slowly on low for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring often with wooden spoon.
Stir in cheese and cook a few minutes more.
Serve with tomato or mushroom sauce or additional cheese and butter.
Goes well with sharp flavored on marinated vegetables.
Excellent leftovers; I like it cold, straight out of the refrigerator.

title: fish stew
directions: Cook onions and potatoes until almost done.
Drain excess liquid, leaving enough to cover vegetables.
Add mackerel, tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Stir. Crack open eggs and drop in a circle in stew.
Do not stir! Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 5.

title: polish pizza
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread thin on round glass platter. Spread Hoffman House shrimp sauce over cream cheese.
Dice and sprinkle over sauce, green pepper, onions, parsley, olives (optional) and mushrooms (optional).
Add broken shrimp, sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese or shredded Cheddar cheese on top. Refrigerate for 5 minutes before serving.
Serve appetizer on Nabisco Wheat Thins.

title: lime punch
directions: Use a gallon jug.
Combine all ingredients in jug.
Stir. Finish filling jug with water and freeze overnight.
It will make a slush punch.

title: kielbasi and pineapple
directions: Cook kielbasi and slice thin.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple and chili sauce.
Mix and level in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add the pineapple, egg and vanilla.
Combine all the dry ingredients and mix into the creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by the teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in grated zucchini.
Sift remaining dry ingredients and add to egg mixture, stirring well.
Fold in nuts and pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour

title: cabbage salad(cole slaw)
directions: In a large bowl, mix together shredded cabbage with salt. Place a plate inside the bowl on top of the cabbage and weigh the plate down to press cabbage down.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Drain off juice from cabbage.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Add chopped onion, if desired.
Pour off grease.
Mix with the potatoes and alphabet soup.
Add dash of salt.
Put in casserole.
Top with the undiluted mushroom soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: cider mill punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan and simmer for 1 to 3 hours.
Strain and serve steaming hot with a cinnamon stick each.
Yield:
14 servings.

title: pineapple inside-out cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cake mix, 1 cup undrained pineapple, eggs, oil and sugar.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed 2 to 4 minutes. Pour in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center springs back.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.
Drain remaining pineapple. Mix sugar, lemon juice and pineapple syrup.
Drizzle over cake to glaze. Top with drained pineapple and cherries.

title: light bread rolls
directions: Put together in order given, beat until smooth.
Let set until light and foamy.
Work in enough flour so it can be handled and kneaded.
Let rise, work down, pinch off what you need. (Keep the rest in refrigerator until needed.) Shape into any shape of roll you want.
Put in a greased pan, let rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Bake at 400°.
Can be frozen.

title: buttermilk glaze
directions: Boil all ingredients 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over cake while still hot.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, margarine and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Mix thoroughly in 9 x 13 pan and smooth out until bottom of pan is covered.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.	Chill while making next layer. Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on top of first layer after it is cool.
Whip pudding, milk and vanilla and spread on top of second layer.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.	Sprinkle with rest of nuts on top.
Chill, then cut into squares.

title: chocolate chips cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla together.
Stir flour, soda, salt and chips together and add to sugar mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli mushroom cheese dip
directions: In large skillet saute onions in butter.
After onions are thoroughly cooked, add mushrooms, cream of mushroom soup, broccoli and cheese.
Stir and simmer until cheese melts and broccoli is no longer frozen.
Serve warm with chips.

title: creamed cauliflower casserole
directions: Break cauliflower into pieces.
Cook until tender.
Drain and place in dish.
Melt margarine and stir in flour; remove from heat and blend in milk.
Bring to a boil, thickening the mixture.
Pour over cauliflower.
Combine salt, stuffing, pepper, water and margarine.
Spoon over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can also use broccoli.

title: vegetarian cheese steak
directions: In a frying pan, slowly cook 4 patties of the vegetarian burgers in 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil until burgers are soft. Using a knife and fork, cut the burgers into small pieces.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream sugar and cooking oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to mixture.
Add mashed bananas and then nuts and vanilla.
Fill muffin tins half full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: kentucky oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and water together and let stand.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Cool, add to vegetables and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Use glass or china bowl.
Will keep up to two weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice and chicken into a baking dish.
Add mushroom soup, celery soup, chicken soup and 1 large envelope of onion soup.
Add just enough broth to make creamy.
Top with 1 large envelope of onion soup.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ham and herb vegetable dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until chilled.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: brownie slowpokes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet.
Combine all ingredients, except walnuts.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing, then cool on wire rack.
Stick 1 walnut into each corner of the slowpokes.
Add frosting (chocolate or your choice) to the top of the slowpoke.

title: louise's asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup to boiling, add jello and stir until dissolved. Add cream cheese and stir until melted. Add mayonnaise and water, beat until blended. Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold. Chill until firm.

title: clam dip
directions: Serve with potato chips.

title: cinnamon-crusted baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Coat an 11 x 7 inch baking dish with cooking spray, and pour water into dish. Arrange apples in prepared dish, and lightly coat apples with cooking spray.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Pour into three 8-inch greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon; brown hamburger and onions.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 325° oven until thickened (approximately) 1 hour.
If you double the recipe, pour off the juice of 1 can of butter beans.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in
order
given;
then blend well. Pour batter
into 2 well-greased 8-inch square pans and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix thoroughly; shape.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Let sit at room temperature 1/2 hour before serving.
Good on crackers and raw vegetables.

title: mustard lamb chops
directions: Set oven for broil.
Trim fat from lamb.
Place lamb on rack in broiler pan.
Mix thyme, mustard and salt; brush 1/2 of mixture evenly over lamb.
Broil with tops about 3 or 4 inches from heat for about 4 minutes or until brown; turn.
Brush remaining mixture over lamb.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes longer for medium doneness. Serves 6.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add soups, Rotel and enchilada mix.
Mix well.
Stir in crushed tortilla chips.
Pour into large baking pan.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: louise's makeshift lasagna
directions: Mix together Ragu sauce, hot water, parsley, oregano, basil and garlic powder and let stand. Cook ground beef until brown, stirring to crumble. Add green pepper and sauce mixture and simmer for 5 minutes. Cook pasta layer in a rectangular pan with hot sauce, using grated Mozzarella between layers of pasta and ending with hot sauce. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese.
Combine margarine and stuffing; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve with hot rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 8.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Combine apples, sugar, cinnamon and flour.

title: hamburger party dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
In blender, mix cheese, tomatoes, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and mix thoroughly.
Cook on high for one hour, stirring often.

title: oatmeal pancakes(fat free)
directions: Put oatmeal and buttermilk in large bowl and mix well.
Let stand 1/2 hour or more then add flour, baking powder, soda, egg whites, vanilla and sweetener to taste.
Blend; spray griddle with Pam and cook.
Top with no sugar syrup.

title: chop suey
directions: Saute steak and onions.
Add juice of bean sprouts and fancy vegetables mixed with soy sauce and molasses and 1 can water. Cook slowly until meat is tender.
Add celery and cook until tender.
Add bean sprouts and Chinese vegetables.
Thicken juice with flour and water mixture and serve over cooked rice.

title: alvin's guacamole dip
directions: Peel and pit California avocado; mash to preferred texture. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend sugar and peanut butter; put 2/3 cup in a baked crust. Beat egg yolks until fluffy.
Add sugar, salt and cornstarch. Beat well.
Add hot milk slowly.
Cook in a saucepan until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Put mixture into crust.

title: hearty havarti chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts.
Dip each chicken breast into salad dressing and bread crumbs, then roll up around cheese and secure with a toothpick.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp and scallop casserole
directions: Saute shrimp and scallops lightly in oil.
Add tomatoes and sauce with green pepper, etc.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix.
Add flour; add oil last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sesame snow peas
directions: To de-stem peas decoratively, pinch off stem end from each pod, pulling strings down pod to remove.
Make a "v-shaped" cut at opposite end of pod.
Heat wok or large skillet over high heat. Add sesame and vegetable oils, swirling to coat sides.
Heat oils about 30 seconds or until hot.
Add onions, ginger root, peas and carrot; briskly toss and stir, keeping vegetables in constant motion for about 4 minutes, or until peas are bright green and crisp-tender.
Stir in soy sauce.
Transfer to warm serving dish; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serve immediately.

title: scallops(good)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make topping by combining bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese in a bowl.
Melt butter and margarine in a medium saucepan.
Saute celery and onions in melted butter and margarine.
Blend in flour to make a paste; cook 1 minute over medium heat.
Gradually add milk, stirring after each addition. Stir wine in sauce.
Add cheese and let it melt, stirring.
Fold in scallops.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and confectioner sugar.
Knead.
Add cream and a few drops of vanilla as needed for moisture.
Roll into balls.
Put in freezer.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Add enough Coke to the juice to make 2 cups.
Heat juice and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Cool.
Add cream cheese, nuts, drained pineapple and cherries.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: crayon soap
directions: Have your child measure the Ivory into a bowl. Add water and stir out all the lumps.
The consistency may seem a little dry, but it will eventually mix together. Add a heavy dose of food coloring until the color looks right and spoon the mixture into the muffin tin to dry.
Make additional batches for different colors. The crayons take from 1 to 2 days to dry.
Pop them from the muffin tin when they are firm to the touch.
Crayon soap washes off all surfaces, including the skin, with a wet washcloth.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine ingredients until well blended. Add chopped onion if desired.
Chill.

title: easy and delicious chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package and cool.
Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on package.
Mix toffee pieces with chocolate pudding.

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix cake mix as on box; put in cake pan.
Put brown sugar over top and sprinkle walnuts over that.
Put miniature marshmallows evenly over top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes its own frosting.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Combine cake mix, almond extract and eggs.
Mix well.
Fold in strawberry pie filling.
Pour into cake pan and bake for 25 to 35 minutes until done.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the chocolate chips and stir until smooth.
Pour frosting over warm cake.
Allow to cool 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots in rounds; dice onion and pepper.
Cook until soft.
Drain and let cool.

title: brussels sprouts oriental
directions: Slice hard ends off sprouts and slice vertically.
Place sesame oil in skillet and heat.
Place Brussels sprouts sliced side down in oil and saute to brown.
Mix tamari sauce and water and pour over sauteed sprouts.
Reduce heat and cook until sprouts are tender and water has cooled down.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix dressing, water and margarine; put in bottom of baking dish (save enough to sprinkle on top).
Sprinkle chicken on top of dressing.
Cook zucchini and onion 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix soup and sour cream and add to zucchini and onion.
Pour over dressing and chicken.
Sprinkle rest of dressing on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together pudding and crushed pineapple.
Add Cool Whip, pecans and marshmallows.

title: strawberry-banana smoothie(a fat-free treat)
directions: Combine strawberry nonfat frozen yogurt,
a
banana and milk. Blend until smooth.

title: dinner in a pumpkin for halloween night(a treat for the whole family)
directions: Cut off top of pumpkin and thoroughly clean out seeds and pulp. Paint an appropriate face on the front of pumpkin with a permanent marking pen or acrylic paint.

title: fresh apple raisin cake
directions: Let raisins soak in hot water 10 to 15 minutes. Drain. Beat eggs; add sugar and oil. Sift all dry ingredients together. Add to egg mixture. Add raisins, nuts and apples; mix.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add rice and dissolved bouillon cubes. Pour over pork chops in casserole dish.
Cover; bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil. Simmer until flavors are blended.
More tomatoes may be added.

title: sweet and creamy dip for fruit
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip and Marshmallow Creme until well mixed.
Serve immediately with fresh fruit to dip in.

title: cranberry lemonade salad
directions: Place 1 cup of the cranberry juice in a small saucepan. Sprinkle gelatin over juice.
Let stand 5 minutes to soften.
Place over low heat and stir constantly until gelatin is dissolved. Combine gelatin mixture, the remaining 1 cup cranberry juice, pineapple juice and frozen lemonade in a metal bowl.
Stir until lemonade is melted.
Chill mixture over a bowl of ice water until the consistency of unbeaten egg white, stirring occasionally. Gently fold in celery, nuts and oranges.
Pour into a 5-cup mold and chill until firm (about 3 hours).

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn bread.
Mix in 8 x 11-inch baking dish or 2-quart dish.
Mix well.
Add corn bread mix and mix well.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: italian homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer for 2 hours.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Mix sugar and melted margarine.
Beat egg in sugar and margarine.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in tight bowl in refrigerator.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Grease muffin tins.
Spoon in dough and bake at 350° until brown.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Cut carrots into rounds and boil in salted water until barely fork tender.
Set aside to cool after draining.
Slice onion and pepper in thin slices.
Mix other ingredients into soup; alternate carrots, onion and pepper slices into bowl.
Pour soup mixture over.
Cover bowl and set in refrigerator for several hours. Tasty with meats.

title: stuffed fig salad
directions: Slit figs and stuff with Gorgonzola cheese.
Place stuffed figs under the broiler to heat through and caramelize the tops. Arrange on a bed of lettuce and drizzle with Balsamic vinegar.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, lemon juice and condensed milk until creamy. Heat oven to 350°.
Use graham cracker crust.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Beat egg whites on high speed until fluffy.
Slowly add 2 tablespoons sugar for each egg white.
Add vanilla and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Cover pie mixture with meringue and bake until slightly brown (about 10 minutes).
Sprinkle crushed pecans on top, if desired.
A little grated lemon rind adds a nice touch.

title: margaret's blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease a 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch glass pan.
Mix ingredients
in	order
given:
egg,
sugar, butter, milk, soda,
baking
powder,
flour
and
blueberries. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar over top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs, slightly beaten, with pumpkin. Combine dry ingredients and blend into pumpkin mixture. Stir in evaporated milk. Pour into chilled pastry shell; bake in hot 425° oven 15 minutes. Reduce heat to moderate 350°; bake 25 to 35 minutes more or until knife inserted 2-inches from edge comes out clean.

title: roasted peppers
directions: Wash peppers and drain well.
Place peppers on cookie sheet, bake about 20 minutes in preheated 450° oven, or until skin becomes blistered and charred.
Turn peppers with tongs every 5 minutes while baking.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Combine water and margarine in pan.
Bring to a boil; add salt and flour all at once.
Remove from heat and stir until mixture is stiff enough to form a ball.
Add cheese and mix well.
Beat in 1 egg at a time until mixture is velvety smooth.
Cover and refrigerate for at least one hour.
Shape into balls (about 1-inch) and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
This will make 25 to 30 puffs.
When cooled, slice and stuff with chicken, turkey, ham or shrimp salad.

title: aunt mollie's marinated carrots
directions: Pour mixture over hot carrots.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: spaghetti chicken
directions: Boil whole chicken until well done.
Save broth.
Remove meat from bones.
Combine chicken, broken pieces of spaghetti, pimentos, onion, soup, chicken broth, salt, pepper and 1 cup cheese.
Toss well in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch casserole (9 x 13-inch can be used).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese over the top and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple with marshmallows and refrigerate overnight. Mix pineapple juice, flour, sugar, egg and vinegar; cook until thick (about 10 minutes), stirring constantly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry-papaya smoothie
directions: Whirl all the ingredients in a blender until smooth. Add ice, if you wish.

title: chili casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add chili.
Cook until heated through, stirring occasionally. Layer the tortilla chips and chili mixture in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, 1 cup butter flavored Crisco and 1/2 cup cool water.
Use pastry dough kneader/cutter and cut until crumbly.
Do not overwork dough!
Roll as desired.
Makes one full pie crust.

title: autumn supper on skewer
directions: Mix orange juice, honey, ginger and marjoram.
Place meat in shallow glass dish.
Pour orange juice mixture over meat.
Cover; refrigerate several hours, turning meat occasionally.
Cook squash in 1 inch boiling salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) for 10 minutes; drain.
Remove meat from marinade.
Reserve marinade.

title: southwestern baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Mix gently.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt margarine and add other ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and onions and cut into large chunks. Put potatoes and onions in a large pot and cover
with water. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: whoopie pies (cookies)
directions: Mix all these ingredients together and drop by spoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Make round and flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Dust
pork chops with flour.
Brown chops in hot fat in a Dutch
oven.
Remove
and
keep
warm.
Drain fat from pan, leaving
about
3 tablespoons.
Saute onion until tender.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and rice.
Return pork chops to tomatoes and rice mixture; simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: good coffee
directions: Place ground coffee (get coffee ground for type coffee maker used) in basket with filter.
Add cocoa and salt.
If coffee maker is not automatic, do not perk longer than 10 minutes.
This makes a strong coffee, so if you desire less strong coffee, cut down on amount of ground coffee.

title: fresh chile rellenos
directions: Slit peppers and cut out membrane and seeds.
Cut cheese into strips and inserted into each chile.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Beat egg yolks until well blended, then fold into egg whites, fold in flour next.
Dip stuffed chilies, one at a time, into batter, lift out with a spoon and transfer into hot grease about 1 1/2-inches deep.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Mix in heavy skillet and simmer until water disappears and nuts have a sugary appearance.
Pour on baking sheet and separate with 2 forks; let cool.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: croghan bologna
directions: Set hamburg aside. Add remaining ingredients together and mix well.
Add to hamburg.
Mix with hands.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Be sure to cover mixture.
Roll into logs.
Place on broiler pan and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool.
Slice and serve. Can be frozen.

title: quick walnut penuche
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring.
Add milk, stirring until boiling.
Remove; cool.
Gradually add confectioners sugar until mixture is of fudge consistency.
Stir in chopped walnuts.
Spread in 8-inch square pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: special k cookies (unbaked)
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil in large saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in Special K.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper; work fast.
Set in pan of warm water if it thickens too fast.

title: kielbasa and potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender with skins on.
cool; cut into slices leaving skins on.
Cut up onion in slices.
Cut kielbasa into circles.

title: pear cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole dish.
Place about 3 cups pears in dish with butter or margarine.
Pour flour mixture over pears. Do not stir. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Melt small amount of butter in large frypan, enough to cover bottom, over medium heat.
Slice sausages and cook slowly until brown.
Turn as needed.
Chop onion, red pepper and parsley while sausage is frying.
Add remaining butter to frypan, if pan is dry, and spoon in onions and red pepper.
Fry until soft.
Measure and stir in flour.
Cook several minutes.
Add tomato paste and mix until smooth with flour blended in.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine dressing, garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Pour over crackers and stir to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crackers are crisp.
Serves 8.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups or about the same as a 14 ounce can of regular condensed milk.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut and cook cabbage until tender; drain.
Dilute soup with milk.
Pour over cabbage in a 13 x 6-inch oblong Pyrex dish.
Mix stuffing as directed on bag.
Put over soup and cabbage.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: country style beef cubed steak
directions: Saut onions in a little bit of vegetable oil in skillet. Sprinkle a little bit of Montreal steak seasoning on cubed steaks. Roll steak in flour. Put steaks in the pan with the onions and oil. Brown well on both sides. Then start pouring beef broth in pan with steak, stirring constantly, until you get the gravy the way you want it. Cover pan. Lower heat and cook slowly (1 hour) so the meat will be tender.

title: mama's baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients in a microwavable bowl.
Cook about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in peanut butter and butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk and eggs all at once, stirring just until moistened. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Immediately brush tops with jelly and dip in peanuts. Serve hot.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine cake mix (reserve 1 cup for topping) with 1/2 cup melted margarine, egg and 2 tablespoons of flour.
Mix and press in bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine and mix pumpkin, ginger, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, salt, milk, white sugar and eggs that have been slightly beaten and pour over crust.
Take reserved cup of cake mix, 1/3 cup flour, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Mix and sprinkle on top of filling.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: brunch casserole(a great christmas morning breakfast)
directions: Prepare the night before.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place bread slices in bottom of dish.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and pepper.
Set aside.
Brown sausage and drain.
Layer sausage and cheese over bread.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Cover; let set overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with fruit juice or fruit cup.

title: slush punch
directions: Pour 6 cups of water into saucepan along with the sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Mix in Jell-O, then combine this with all the remaining ingredients, except the ginger ale.
Mix well and freeze in gallon jugs.
Remove from freezer about 4 hours before serving time (punch should be slushy).
Add 1 large ginger ale per 1 gallon punch.

title: maple custard
directions: Combine above ingredients in a bowl.
Pour evenly into 4 individual baking dishes.
Set in a pan with 1 inch of hot water. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 4 servings as part of midday meal.
Supplement as required.

title: vi's banana cake
directions: Cream together shortening (I use butter), sugar and eggs. Beat in sifted flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in buttermilk, mashed bananas and pecan pieces.
Pour into layer pans or a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in an oblong pan or in layers for 25 minutes.
Use a dark chocolate frosting.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine all wet ingredients and mix on low speed for 1 minute.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda; blend in 1/3 cup of melted butter.
Add boiling water and stir until well blended.
Mix in sugar, eggs and remaining butter; blend in flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chunks.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: saucy baked beans
directions: Brown bacon lightly. Drain; combine ingredients and pour into casserole.
Bake in moderate oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour to brown.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
Add well beaten egg and salt and flour.
Heat 1 tablespoon cooking oil in frying pan. Drop spoonfuls of mixture into hot fat.
Fry golden brown.
Serve as is or with sour cream or applesauce.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets; reserve 1/2 cup liquid.

In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; mix well. Gradually stir in reserved beet liquid, vinegar and salt. Bring to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes or until thickened and translucent. Add beets and simmer very slowly, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add butter and bring to a boil.
Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour in 9-inch unbaked crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 300° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Measure flour by sifting. Blend all dry ingredients. Stir in preceding mixture. Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. (Puffs at first, then flattens.)

title: angel wings
directions: Cook sugar, butter, egg and dates over low heat, stirring often.
Cook until thick.
Remove and cool.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies cereal.
Form into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: basic recipe for fruit cake(nice, moist cake)
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and egg together.
Stir in applesauce (just a little).
Add flour, salt, spices, soda and raisins.
Add as much candied fruit, dates and nuts as you wish for fruit cake. For the cake with all the fruit, line your loaf pans with wax paper and grease well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
In a 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Test in 1/2 hour.

title: berry or fruit muffins
directions: Mix all together and fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Wash and cut squash in half lengthwise.
Cook in salted water just until tender; drain.
Scrape out pulp, leaving a shell.
Save pulp.
Brown meat; add bell pepper, onion, tomato sauce and Accent.
Cook until meat changes color.
Add pulp; mix well. Spoon meat mixture inside squash shells.
Place squash in baking dish.
Cover; bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; top with grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: quiche
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, eggs and milk.
Add ham, cheese (chopped or shredded), and spinach (that has been drained).
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add Karo and buttermilk.
Bake in ungreased No. 2 size cans for 1 hour at 350°; fill cans 2/3 full.
Let cool for 30 minutes before turning out of cans.
Cream cheese may be spread on the bread.

title: sweetheart punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve drink mix and sugar in 2 quarts of cold water.
Stir well.
Add pineapple juice to gelatin mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.
Yields 35 servings.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add egg yolks.
Beat until creamy, add dry ingredients with milk.
Beat well.
Add beaten egg whites until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in 350° oven 1 1/4 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Remove from pan.
Flour meat and brown on each side.
Add bouillon and salt.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Stir in sour cream, mushrooms and onions.
Serve over rice.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add lemon juice and beat well.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.
Cover with chilled blueberries.

title: cranberry heavenly hash
directions: Blend cheese, mayo and sugar.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Blend in nuts and Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Tastier when firm but not solid.

title: vineyard chicken
directions: Brown noodles in butter.
Add rice and bouillon.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine celery soup and milk. Add onion and broccoli.
Bring
to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: ham apetillas
directions: Combine first four ingredients; spread evenly on tortillas. Arrange four ham slices over each tortilla; tightly roll up and wrap each individually in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch slices.
Yield:
8 1/2 dozen.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix vinegar, mustard, sugar and salt to Miracle Whip.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes to thicken.
Pour over warm cooked potatoes.
Add eggs, onion and celery seed.
Mix well, then refrigerate.

title: heart-smart blueberry muffins
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine the wet ingredients and blend.
Add to the wet ingredients to the dry.
Fold in your choice of fruit.
Pour into a greased muffin pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: candy turtles
directions: Melt caramels with cream over hot water.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Arrange pecan halves in groups of 3 on lightly greased baking sheet (1 for head and 2 for legs).
Spoon melted caramel over nuts, leaving tips showing.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove from water; stir until smooth. Cool.
Spread over caramel of turtles (do not cover nut tips). Makes 24 turtles.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop lettuce and tomatoes, refrigerate.
Brown ground beef, drain.
Add taco seasoning and beans to ground beef.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until cold.
When ready to serve, add hamburger mixture, cheese and crushed Doritos to lettuce and tomatoes.
Pour dressing over top and mix well.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, crushed peanuts, sugar and margarine.
Press in pie pan.
Beat until very smooth the cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in 8 ounces of the Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Spread the remaining Cool Whip over the peanut butter filling and garnish with chopped nuts, then drizzle hot fudge.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins and 3 cups water down to 1 cup water.
When cooled, add rest of ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 15-inch pan until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake at 350°.

title: spicy apple sauerkraut with spareribs for 50
directions: Arrange ribs in roasting pans.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove spareribs from pan; drain off excess fat.
Arrange apples, kraut, caraway seed and sugar in alternating layers in same roasting pans.
Pour vinegar over all.
Place partially cooked spareribs on top of kraut and bake 1 hour longer. Serves 50 people.

title: beef macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and bell pepper in skillet. Drain grease. Add cream of mushroom soup, both steak sauces, ketchup and chili powder. Add 1 cup water. Simmer until desired taste. Mix together macaroni and sauce. Put in 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until it bubbles. Cover with cheese.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk; let thicken slightly.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Layer grahams in 9 x 13-inch pan alternately with pudding mix.
Top with icing.

title: buckeyes
directions: In a medium bowl, mix powdered sugar, peanut butter and butter until well blended, kneading with hands if necessary. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and place in a single layer in a jelly roll pan. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.

title: rhubarb-strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, cinnamon and mace.
In separate bowl, stir rhubarb and strawberries together.
Pour half of rhubarb-strawberry mixture into pastry shell; sprinkle with half the sugar mixture.
Repeat with remaining mixtures.
Dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Slit to release steam.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Beat egg yolks first.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients (except 1/2 cup flour) alternating with buttermilk to which soda has been added.
(Let soda rise to top of cup.)
Dredge fruits in 1/2 cup flour.
Add to mixture. Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 225° for 30 minutes, then bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cup pie
directions: Follow directions for pudding, then mix with peanut butter and 1 cup whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Put remainder of whipped topping on pie.
Garnish with chocolate chips or sprinkles.
Freeze for 2 to 3 hours, then serve.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook sausage 20 minutes and drain excess fat.
Cook pastas according to directions on package.
Saute mushrooms, onions and peppers in butter.
In an 8 x 8-inch baking dish, layer as follows:
pastas, sausage, mushroom mixture, sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: super jelgurt salad
directions: Heat water until boiling.
Stir in gelatin and stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Add yogurt and stir until dissolved.
Pour in can of pineapple, including juice.
Stir until well blended. Pour into mold or molds.
Chill until set.
This salad may be made with a variety of flavors of yogurt, fruit and gelatin.

title: grandmother lou's tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar, butter and shortening until fluffy. Add egg, vanilla, flour, salt, tartar and soda. Mix and roll into balls the size of a walnut. Place on cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon pineapple with juice evenly over cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter on cake mix.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake is done.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour hot water over oatmeal in large bowl.
Add shortening, salt and molasses.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Stir in about 2 cups of the flour.
Add yeast and mix well.
Continue to stir in remaining flour, gradually, until dough springs back when pressed with finger.
Let rise to double the amount.
Knead down.
Let rise and form into two loaves.
Let rise and bake at 325° about 45 minutes.

title: tequila barbecue sauce
directions: In a 5 qt. saucepan, combine the pineapple juice, tomato paste, tequila, lemon juice, vinegar, garlic, and hot sauce. Bring to boil over medium heat and stir often until reduced to 2 cups, about 20 minutes. Use sauce, or refrigerate, covered tightly, for up to 2 weeks.

title: chicken and sausage
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil until lightly browned on both sides.
Remove from skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic and saute until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Add Italian sausage and brown, then add all 3 in a baking dish.
Pour over chicken broth and white wine.
Add spices and seasoned pepper.
Cover loosely and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve over rice.

title: greasy bread
directions: If bacon is sliced, cut into 1 to 2-inch chunks; if not sliced, dice into squares.
Fry bacon alone until entirely cooked. Now add veggies.
Cook until soft.
Serve on sub rolls or hot dog rolls.
Don't drain grease while cooking; if you do, put it on the bread.
Great for open fires and camping.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine
all
ingredients except nuts in a large mixing bowl. Beat
at low speed for 30 seconds, and medium speed for 2 minutes; stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.	Bake at 350°
for
50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: buttermilk custard pie
directions: Prepare pastry crust.
Melt butter or margarine; cool.
Beat egg yolks slightly, stir in sugar, flour and salt.
Add butter or margarine, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; fold into buttermilk mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°, bake 15 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted in pie center comes out clean and pie is golden brown.
Cool and chill before serving.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs and mix well.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Add coconut.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: hot relish for peas
directions: Chop vegetables.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Can in jars or eat.

title: janet's chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix
first
3 ingredients together.
Add dab of milk to make smooth
consistency.
Open can of rolls and cut each roll in half to
make
triangles.
Drop about a teaspoonful of chicken mixture onto center of triangle; fold corners up (like diaper). Bake
according
to
directions
on roll package, or until lightly browned.

title: peach cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla and keep stirring all the time.
Add to all this the can of peaches (without its juice) and the nuts. Put in any pan you want and bake in a 325° oven for about 70 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: frozen berry dessert
directions: In a large bowl mix berries, egg whites, sugar and lemon juice.
Beat for 15 minutes.
Whip whipping cream and then fold into fruit mixture.
Spread over cooled crumb crust and top with reserved crumbs.
Freeze.
After frozen, keep covered.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: Prepare cheesecake mixture as directed on box. Crumble 1/2 package cookies and add to mixture.
Pour cheesecake into chocolate crust.
Add remaining cookies around edge of pie crust.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and let come to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sinful kahlua trifle(a winner; easy)
directions: Makes one tall trifle or two normal bowl trifles.

title: mother's fruit punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 4 cups of boiling water.
Dissolve sugar in 6 cups of hot water and add to Jell-O mixture.
Add frozen orange juice and lemonade (diluted according to directions).
Add pineapple juice.
Dilute with additional water if too strong to taste.
Chill for several hours.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and pour over sherbet placed in punch bowl.
Makes about 3 1/2 gallons or 60 cups.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done, then place it in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Cook the broccoli spears and place on top of chicken.
In small bowl mix soup, Miracle Whip and lemon juice. Pour this mixture over the chicken and broccoli.
In a small bowl mix bread crumbs, cheese (enough to your liking) and enough melted margarine to make crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of chicken.
Bake until brown and heated through at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pecans over pan. Sprinkle coconut over pecans.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt and mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue scallops
directions: Place oil in frying pan.
Brown scallops, don't burn them. After browning, place in baking dish.
With the oil that's left in pan, simmer onions, peppers and garlic until soft.
Add tomato paste, water and ketchup.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over scallops and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Heat margarine in deep skillet. Add onion, garlic and remainder of zucchini and water.
Cover and simmer gently 10 minutes.
Stir with wooden spoon while cooking. Remove from heat; add all remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Turn into blender for 30 seconds.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Combine mayonnaise and vinegar in bowl. Whip with wire whisk until smooth. Add 2 peeled and sliced cucumbers. Salt and pepper to taste. Stir well. Chill before serving.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve over tossed green salad. Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and cook sausage in a fry pan. Drain and set aside. In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, add milk, salt and mustard. In a greased baking dish, layer bread, sausage and cheese. Pour egg mixture over top of ingredients. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: wisconsin potato cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat. Saute celery and onion until tender. Add potatoes and broth. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 12 minutes. Stir in milk and seasonings. Add the cheese and heat only until melted. Garnish with parsley and cheese. Yield: 8 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon, hamburger and onions lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or crock-pot medium heat 8 hours.
Great.

title: american piece of pie
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water in a large bowl.
Add egg and next five ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Gradually add flour. Knead and let rise.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water.
Grease a casserole dish.
Put noodles, meat and onion in layers.
Pour over the top the cream of chicken soup to which you have added 1/2 cup milk.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: jumbo oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together applesauce and sugar until light and fluffy; blend in egg whites and vanilla.
Add combined flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.

Stir in oats, raisins or chips; drop dough by level 1/3 cup measures onto greased cookie sheet about 4 inches apart and 2 1/2 inches from edge of cookie sheet (or heaping tablespoonfuls about 3 inches apart and 1 1/2 inches from edge of cookie sheet).
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 17 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 1 dozen 4 1/2-inch cookies or 2 dozen 3 1/2-inch cookies.

title: quick and easy egg rollschina
directions: Cook all the vegetables in a lightly greased pan and drain well. In a large bowl, combine the beef, vegetables, egg and a pinch of salt and pepper. Mix thoroughly. Follow wrapping instructions on egg roll wrapper pkg. Pan fry or deep fry the rolls until light brown.

title: white bean chili
directions: Cover chicken with cold water and bring to simmer.
Cook until tender, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and dice into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: pastry crust
directions: Place flour and salt in a bowl.
Add butter.
With fingertips only, mix to a bread crumb consistency.
Mix in egg yolk and lemon juice.
With a knife, cut in 1 teaspoon water, adding a little more if necessary to form a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead gently into a small ball.
If using to make a pie, roll out to size of pie plate.
Carefully line pie plate with crust. Prick base with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes bottom crust for one 8-inch pie.

title: tamale balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, using only 2 cups V-8 juice, leaving the rest of the juice and the 4 teaspoons of chili powder for the sauce.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer each ingredient, one at a time, starting with refried beans and ending with salsa or tomatoes. Serve with chips.

title: venus di milo soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add rest of ingredients to soup pot and simmer slowly, about 1 hour.

title: gentlemen's lemon pie
directions: Add flour to sugar and cream thoroughly with butter. Add unbeaten eggs and beat well.
Add lemon juice and rind and beat in well.
Pour into your favorite pie crust and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut squash in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Pare squash.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix dry ingredients.
Arrange squash in ungreased baking pan 11 x 7-inch and top with sliced apples.
Sprinkle sugar mixture on top; pour melted butter around.
Cover with foil.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk;
let stand for 30 minutes. Stir together
until
thoroughly
blended the flour, soda and baking powder.
Add
melted
butter,
sugar and egg to oatmeal mixture and
blend thoroughly.
Stir in dry ingredients, just until blended.
Spoon
batter
into greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pans, filling
each
about
2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes
or
until browned and tops spring back when lightly touched.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: taco ranch stew
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; drain and set aside.
Put into a crock-pot: beans, corn, tomatoes, Ro-Tel, dry mixes, meat and onion.
Heat thoroughly.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Wash, core and quarter apples.
Do not peel.
Combine apples and juice.
Put in lightly oiled crock-pot; cover.
Cook on low 10 to 18 hours; on high 2 to 4 hours.
Put apples through sieve or food mill.
Add spices (1 cup sugar per pint; 1 teaspoon cinnamon per pint and 1/2 teaspoon allspice per pint).
Stir well and return to crock-pot.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours.
Stir every 2 hours.
Remove cover after 2 hours to allow fruit to cook down. Put in sterile jars.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar; add tomato soup to which is added soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, baking powder, flour, raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes; tube pan, 50 to 60 minutes.
Grease and flour pans.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Not for anyone watching their cholesterol!

title: chocolate-strawberry torte
directions: Bring to a boil and cook until slightly thick the sliced strawberries, sugar, water, cornstarch and a few drops red food coloring.
Set aside and let cool completely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain well.
Combine other ingredients, except crackers, to make sauce.
Place broccoli in sauce and stir.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
About 15 minutes before it's done, place cracker crumbs on top.

title: val's salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon (remove skin and bone). Combine with next
8 ingredients, mixing well. Chill several hours. Shape into log or ball and roll in chopped nuts, or serve as spread with crackers. Very good.

title: chocolate milk
directions: Pour the milk into the glass.
Put chocolate syrup or powder into glass.
Then stir.

title: tuna crescentwiches
directions: Combine tuna, celery, egg, onion and mayonnaise together. Separate
crescent rolls, leaving two triangles together. Put a spoonful of mixture in half of a rectangle.
Cover with a slice of
cheese.
Fold
roll
in half over the mixture and press sides together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: carrot coconut bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream, stir until smooth. Add cream of coconut, chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: healthy squash casserole
directions: Mash squash. Crumble bread.
Put aside 1/3 of the bread crumbs.
Mix all other ingredients and put into a large baking dish.
Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown on top (about 20 to 30 minutes).

title: chop suey cake
directions: Blend together flour, sugar, eggs, baking soda, pineapple and nuts by hand.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, vanilla, margarine and 10-X sugar for topping.
Cover cake with topping while cake is hot and refrigerate.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons of margarine until soft, stir in flour and add water and cook to a boil.
Blend in asparagus, cheese and eggs.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with remaining margarine and sprinkle on cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add beans, catsup, vinegar, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Put in casserole dish. Top with bacon strips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peaches and cream shortcake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, egg, milk, oleo and pudding (not instant).
Beat mixture for 2 minutes on medium speed of mixer.
Pour into a 10-inch pie plate (greased).
Place well drained peaches over mixture (save juice).
Combine cream cheese, sugar and the reserved juice.
Spoon over peaches.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cream cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Filling will appear soft.

title: washington nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients (except nuts) in mixing bowl until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake until firm, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: raisin pumpkin crisps
directions: Rinse and drain raisins.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg and beat well.
Stir in pumpkin.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: bacalhau a gomes-sa
directions: Place olive oil in heavy skillet.
Add onion rings and saute until very lightly browned and transparent.
Do not overcook.
Add garlic, pepper, bay leaf and vinegar.
Set aside.

title: granola chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Combine the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger and granola.
Stir into the butter mixture, combining thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove from sheets.
Cool on racks. Makes 36 cookies.

title: mushroom topped mini meat loaves(8 or 10)
directions: Mix ground meats with egg, seasonings and tomato juice.
Add crumbs.
Saute onion and garlic in a little butter.
Add chives. Shape individual loaves.
Place side by side on broiler-type pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Have ready mushroom caps dipped in melted butter.
Secure with toothpick on top of each loaf.
Bake additional 15 minutes.

title: oriental beef strips
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch strips (1/8 x 3-inches).
Brown in heavy skillet; add water to browned steak.
Combine other ingredients and add to pan, except cornstarch.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 45 minutes until meat is tender.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: caramel pie
directions: Melt and brown 1/2 cup sugar.
Add hot water and cook 3 minutes.
Sift flour and 1 cup sugar.
Add milk and egg yolks, stir.
Add hot mixture, cook until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites until
Slightly stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Top pie and brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until bright green and tender; drain and place in baking dish.
Heat remaining ingredients, except croutons. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: sparkling grape juice
directions: Prepare per instructions on juice container except substitute Sprite or 7-Up for water.
Serve immediately.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: taco beef noodle bake
directions: Brown chuck, stirring often, and drain.
Add onion, tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning mix.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Combine noodles, Ricotta cheese, sour cream, flour and green onion; mix well.
Spoon noodle mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake for 5 additional minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8. Recipe may be halved and it also freezes well.
Prepare recipe as indicated all the way up to the cooking.

title: bette's candy recipe
directions: Melt butter on cookie sheet.
Stir in pecans.
Place in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir a few times.
Mix with melted chocolate.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed cookie sheet or drop in a peanut cup mold.

title: cheesy bean and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Combine rice and kidney beans; set aside.
In a large skillet, melt butter; add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes (reserving 1/3 cup liquid), chili powder and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, chopping up tomatoes and stirring.
Place 1/2 of rice mixture on bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of sliced cheese and 1/3 of tomato mixture.
Repeat cheese and tomato layers.
Top with remaining rice mixture and remaining 1/3 cup liquid.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: kalua pig
directions: Pat pork thoroughly with salt and place fat side up in roasting pan or crock pot.
Combine water with liquid smoke and pour over meat.
Cover and either roast at 400° for 3 hours or until tender, or slow cook on high for 4-5 hours until pork falls apart.
Remove from water and shred in serving dish.

title: potato soup
directions: Scald 2 cups milk.
Add potatoes; beat well.
Add seasonings; blend butter and flour.
Add egg and remaining milk.
Drop from teaspoon into hot soup.
Cover pan and cook for about 10 minutes. Serves 2.

title: cheesy gherkin ham roll-ups
directions: Place one halved sweet gherkin lengthwise onto each piece of ham.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up ham.
Slice and secure with wooden toothpick.
Place in 9-inch square glass baking dish. Cover.
Microwave on High (9) for 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.
Total cooking time is 3 minutes.
Makes 14 appetizers.

title: tomato-celery soup
directions: Dice small onion and celery stalks.
Melt butter in frypan. Saute onion and celery in butter and lemon juice.
Drain.

title: shrimp spread
directions: In a small mixing bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill at least 12 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Makes about 3 cups.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cheesy-bacon spread(catch-a-man dip)
directions: Grate cheese, then add all remaining ingredients.
Add salt if desired, however, this gets saltier as it blends together.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato soup and 1/2 can water.
Add mushroom soup and 3/4 can water; add to noodles.
Top with cheese (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese is melted and brown.

title: nutritious strawberry lemonade
directions: Put all ingredients except berries in a blender.
Cover and run on high until mixed well.
Add berries and run on high for just 20 seconds.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk and butter in the top of a double boiler.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in whipped and grated chocolate.
Pour into pastry shell and refrigerate.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk and raisins in 2-quart saucepan.
Cover and cook slowly over low heat until rice is tender, about 40 to 50 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Beat egg yolks lightly with granulated sugar.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir into hot rice mixture.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Whip egg whites until foamy, then whip in alternately confectioners sugar and cream of tartar until stiff.
Spoon meringue on top of pudding.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: just trash
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips.
Set aside. Mix cereal, raisins and nuts.
Combine both mixtures in large bowl.
Dump into trash bag with powdered sugar and shake until coated.

title: candied nuts
directions: Mix the sugar, cinnamon and canned milk together in a saucepan.
Boil to soft ball stage (236°) or approximately 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir until it can no longer be stirred.
Separate on waxed paper.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries until tender in 1 cup water.
Add 2 cups sugar.
Dissolve red and orange jello with 3
cups boiling water. Pour jello in 13 x 9-inch glass pan and add cranberry mixture, celery, drained pineapple, nuts and mandarin oranges.
Chill overnight or longer.

title: simmons' japanese morning delight
directions: Beat eggs in a medium size bowl until frothy.
Stir in bean sprouts, mushrooms, onion, pepper, soy sauce and garlic powder.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and return to cooking pot; set aside.
In medium skillet over medium-high heat melt 1 tablespoon butter. Add beef and onion; cook about 2 minutes or until beef loses its pink color, stirring often.
Drain off all fat.
Stir tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper into meat mixture; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer uncovered 3 minutes; set aside.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: In a large serving bowl, toss all ingredients with the shredded cabbage and shredded carrots.

title: almost instant pierogis
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and return to pot.
Add cheese to potatoes and mash until cheese melts.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onions and cook 10 to 15 minutes, stirring several times until tender, but not browned.

title: spicy oven fried chicken
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt, chili powder, oregano and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in milk; coat with corn meal mixture. Place chicken in a large shallow pan; drizzle butter over chicken. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for about 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: mama's coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in slightly browned pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until firm.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Beat ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown beef with onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve topped with crushed tortilla chips.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Drain zucchini; combine with egg and a dash of salt and pepper.
Sift flour and baking powder over mixture and mix well. Heat a lightly oiled skillet.
Drop batter by 1/4 cup onto skillet.
Fry until lightly browned; turn and brown other side. Brush finished pancakes with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: boiled picnic ham
directions: Cover ham with water in a kettle.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Cool in water.
Remove.
Drain well.
Slice.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil until soft ball stage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper.
Work fast, cools quickly!

title: saturday's ham and egg scramble
directions: Combine ham and butter in an 8-inch round dish covered with wax paper.
Cook at High 2 to 3 minutes; stir once.
Combine cream cheese and milk; blend in eggs, salt and pepper.
Add to ham. Cook, covered, at Medium for 5 to 6 minutes or until eggs are almost set.
Stir twice.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: holiday nachos
directions: Brown ground beef and follow directions on seasoning mix package.
When browning beef and mix, add several tablespoons of salsa for extra flavor.
Place tortilla style nacho chips on baking sheet.
Put seasoned beef over nachos.
Place shredded Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve warm with sour cream and salsa on the side.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Use 1/3 cup to 1 cup boiling water.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and reserve 1 cup pineapple juice.
Mix fruit and sprinkle pudding over it.
Mix Tang with pineapple juice and pour over fruit.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, cut up banana and stir in.

title: lunch box peanut oatmeal candies
directions: In a medium saucepan, over low heat, melt butter or margarine. In a small bowl, stir together sugar and cocoa.
Add to melted butter or margarine in saucepan; stir to blend.
Stir in milk. Bring mixture to a full boil.
Let boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Stir in oats.
Beat with a wooden spoon until mixture begins to harden, about 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool completely.
Wrap and pack for lunch.
Be sure to beat for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter honey muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt and brown sugar.
In another bowl, combine melted butter, peanut butter, eggs, honey, vanilla and milk.
Combine the two mixtures, pouring the liquid ingredients into the dry.
Stir only until blended.
Spoon into buttered muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool a minute before removing from pan.
Serve slightly warm.

title: rainbow cake
directions: These bars have a firm shortbread crust and a very lemony filling, making them a perfect finish for a spicy meal like this Mexican picnic.
We also love them with afternoon tea.

title: lazy man enchiladas
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion and seasoning.
Add salsa and refried beans.
Pour 1/2 can of enchilada sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay 4 tortillas in bottom of pan until covered.
Spoon 1/2 beef mixture over tortillas.
Top with 1/2 of the olives and 1/4 of the grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining tortillas, beef mixture and olives.
Pour the rest of the can of enchilada sauce; top off with remaining cheese.
Heat in low oven or microwave until heated through and/or cheese is melted.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add milk all at once.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly, about 1 minute.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
In medium saucepan, dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Bring to a boil, add broccoli and cook according to package directions; do not drain.
Add broccoli and
cooking liquid to cheese mixture; stir until well blended.
Yields 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: barb's cheesecake
directions: Combine butter and crumbs.
Press 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix gelatin and boiling water.
Sit in refrigerator to cool.

title: easy divinity
directions: Place marshmallow cream in large bowl.
Combine water, sugar and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Mix well and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Put lid on pan and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour syrup over marshmallow cream.
Stir until mixture loses its gloss.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper. Store in an airtight container.

title: country kitchen cheese soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, parsley flakes and bouillon cube and pepper.
Simmer for about 30 minutes. Gradually add the milk that has been mixed with the flour.
Add to the vegetables and simmer until thickened.
Add the ham and cheese. Stir until melted.
Serves 4.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Next, place shredded chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup. curry powder, and mayonnaise.
Place on top of chicken.
Next, slice cheese and place on top.
Finally, spread cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350 until bubbly.

title: cold veggie pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls in a 12 x 15-inch pan; flatten and shape to fit pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°, or until brown. Cool.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package and drain.
Prepare gravy mix as directed on package. Stir in parsley.
In 13 x 9-inch pan spread 1 cup tomato sauce. Cover with a layer of lasagna noodles, using half the noodles. Top with half the chicken and half the Mozzarella cheese.
Pour half of the gravy over the top and spread.
Add another layer of noodles, 1 cup of tomato sauce, remaining chicken and gravy, ending with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered about 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
For ease in serving, let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into serving portions.

title: fresh corn bell pepper relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve
with pork or beef.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator up
to
days.
Yields
2 1/2 cups (about 6 calories per tablespoon).

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine egg, bread crumbs, onion, relish, salad dressing, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well.
On waxed paper, pat mixture to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Top with sauerkraut and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Using waxed paper to lift rectangle, roll up meat jelly-roll style, beginning with short side.
Press ends to seal.
Place roll, seam side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 3 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until it falls off the bone.
Reserve broth.
Mix flour with shortening, salt and ice cool water as you would to make pie crust dough.
Pinch off small balls and roll each real thin.
Cut into strips and drop into boiling chicken broth.
(I break my strips into even smaller pieces.
You can use canned broth also.)
Boil for 20 minutes or until dumplings are done. Shred chicken and drop in dumpling mixture (as much chicken as you like).

title: macaroni and cheese with salsa
directions: Boil water first. Cook noodles, drain noodles and pour cheese and salsa and mix together.

title: poppyseed bread
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients in a large bowl; beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.

Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch by 4-inch by 3-inch loaf pans; bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean Pour orange glaze over poppyseed bread after it has cooled 5 minutes.
Cool 5 more minutes and remove from pans; place on rack to finish cooling.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Combine next 4 ingredients and cook until marshmallows are melted.
Stir well and spread on hot cake.
Bring next 3 ingredients together and boil, adding chocolate chips last and stirring until melted.
Spread over coconut topping.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes on medium speed with an electric mixer.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread crushed onion rings evenly over the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes in 300° oven.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place chicken in glass baking dish. Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Leave covered first 20 to 30 minutes.
Baste several times.
Yields 4 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter; mix well.
Add flour mixture, baking powder and salt to butter and sugar.
Add milk and mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flavor. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Cook on 375° until brown.
Let cool and frost.

title: frozen imitation raspberry jam
directions: Boil tomatoes and sugar 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Pour into freezer containers and put in freezer.
Needs about 1/2 hour to defrost.
Good on toast.

title: pork chop suey
directions: Brown pork in oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add celery, onion, green pepper, salt, garlic and 1 cup liquid drained from vegetables.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat until tender, about 25 minutes.
Add vegetables and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until heated through, about 10 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch.
Cook until thickened.
Season with soy sauce.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and other ingredients, adding oatmeal and nuts last. Form into a roll and wrap in wax paper.
Place in freezer overnight.
Slice and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Add bread crumbs to milk and let stand a few minutes.
Mix with ground beef, egg, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and onion; shape into meat loaf.
Put into a baking loaf pan.
Combine ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, salt and water and mix.
Spoon this mixture over the meat loaf.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients well. Add wafers.
Cook at 350° in a loaf or layer pan.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, place rice, soup, water and mushrooms with juice.
Pour on sauteed onion and celery.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: pork chops cooked with sour cream
directions: Before frying, rub each pork chop with prepared mustard.
Then roll chops in flour.
In deep skillet, fry in butter until brown. Add chicken stock and onions.
Simmer, covered, on low heat for 1 hour.
Pour off liquid.
To this, add the sour cream.
Mix well. Don't let sauce boil after adding cream.
Sour cream should be at room temperature when added to the pan liquid.
Pour sauce over chops.

title: jam cake
directions: Spray Pam in 3 pans.
Cook at 300° or 325° until firm.
Cook 3 more pans and that will be 2 cakes.

title: jane's zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir to blend thoroughly.
Break eggs into mixer bowl; beat well.
Add vanilla, then oil, then sugar.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Add flour mixture slowly and blend well.
Mix in nuts.
Divide batter into three 1 1/3-cup loaf pans.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Dice all vegetables and fruit.
(I used my blender).
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender and at desired thickness.

title: country mashed potatoes
directions: Steam potatoes; add butter and mash.
Salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Put in cheese and crumbled bacon to taste.

title: banana chocolate chip bars
directions: Beat butter, brown sugar and nutmeg together until creamy. Beat in bananas and vanilla.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, wheat germ, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, beating well.
By hand, stir in chocolate chips and 1/2 of nuts.
Spread mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon; spread over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Makes about 3 dozen bars.

title: mildred's chocolate pie
directions: Cook the first six ingredients until thick; add vanilla. Reserve whites for meringue.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix all together except bananas and strawberries 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Add bananas and strawberries just before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
