Mash bananas into creamed mixture.
Beat in eggs (as eggs are added the mixture will normally separate or look curdled).
Add biscuit mix and nuts. Stir until well mixed; pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cans of corn, cornbread mix and chilies.
Mix with a fork.
Add onion and sugar. Add beaten eggs and spread evenly in pan.
Drop sour cream by spoonfuls on top and fold in gently.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until firm.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Bring oil, vinegar, sugar and salt to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator 6 weeks or more.

title: salt substitute from heloise
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in clean jar and store in dry place.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown hamburger meat with spices.
Add tomato sauce, Ro-Tel, chili and cooked noodles.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Mix well. Press into pan and bake until browned.

title: crabmeat mousse
directions: Combine everything and heat.
While warm, stir in gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold; refrigerate until firm.
Turn on platter and serve with Ritz or Escort crackers.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix ingredients together; cover.
Put in refrigerator 24 hours.
Put in container; stir once or twice.
Freeze or keep in fridge.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk, butter and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Let boil 4 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch glass bowl.
Let it get hard.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Lay pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake for 15 to 30 minutes to brown meat.
Can be cooked in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours on low setting.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: In a large bowl, blend sugars with butter, egg and vanilla. Beat thoroughly. Stir in flour and salt. Spread on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake
at 325° for approximately 25 minutes. Spread while hot with chocolate chips and nuts.

title: easy supper casserole
directions: Grease 8-inch square baking dish.
Add dry noodles.
Brown meat and onion.
Drain off any grease.
Put meat mixture over noodles. Mix spaghetti sauce and water and pour over noodles and meat.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and add cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes more to melt cheese.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix milk, salt, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Scald in saucepan and let mixture cool.
Dissolve yeast in the water and sugar.
Add to the milk mixture.
Add the flour; mix well.
Let the dough rise twice.
Make rolls.
Put into pans and let rise again.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans for 40 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pans; cool on cake rack.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, pepper, olives, onion, salt, milk and eggs. Pour 1/2 cup more tomato juice on top.
Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: no-crust coconut pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Add dry ingredients to eggs, butter and coconut.
Gradually add milk.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie plates.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pistachio-pineapple delight
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into a bowl.
Add the pudding mix. Beat with a wire whisk, rotary beater or electric mixer at lowest speed until well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Spoon into shallow dish or dessert cups. Pudding will be soft-set and ready to eat in 5 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: orange sweet potatoes(no fat)
directions: Boil potatoes 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove skins and discard.
Mash pulp; add remaining ingredients and whip until fluffy.

title: mom's french dressing
directions: Mix soup, sugar or honey, salt, mustard and paprika in blender or food processor.
Slowly add vinegar and oil, one teaspoon at a time, constantly processing.
Add onions and peppers.
Refrigerate.

title: pat's do not peek chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly over a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the mushroom and celery soup together in small bowl.
Combine margarine and water.
Pour over rice.
Lay pieces of chicken on rice and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal with foil; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Do not peek during baking time.
Serves 6.

title: fluffy yam souffle
directions: Drain and mash yams in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients, except marshmallows, and mix well.
Put into large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Top casserole with marshmallows and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: orzo salad
directions: Add ingredients in order; mix together until well mixed and refrigerate.
Serve with a dollop of Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Season squash with salt and pepper.
Add carrot, onion, pimento, soup and sour cream.
Mix margarine and dressing mix. Place 1/2 of the dressing mix in a greased casserole dish, add squash mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce; chill several hours. Before serving, toss together with lettuce.
Season to taste.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on a serving platter.
Mash avocados and mix with lemon juice.
Spread over bean dip.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Spread over avocados.
Chop green onions and sprinkle over mixture.
Add chopped tomatoes, black olives, lettuce and jalapenos.
Top with shredded cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Chop 1 package of ham (fine) and put in a bowl.
Chop the other package of ham (fine) in another bowl and set aside.
Mix cream cheese, 1 package ham, onion, hot sauce and Worcestershire.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Roll ball into other package of ham to cover.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: kix or cocoa puffs wrap around snack
directions: Heat sugar and corn syrup to boiling in a 3 quart saucepan over medium heat stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until blended.
Stir in cereal.
Cool slightly.
Lightly butter hands.
Shape 2 Tbsp. of cereal mixture into a ball around each gumdrop.
Roll ball into colored sugar if desired.

title: boo's italian potatoes
directions: Boil whole potatoes, with peeling, until a full rolling boil. Remove from heat and cover.
Let them sit for 20 minutes, then slice them about 1/4-inch thick and place on cookie sheet.
Salt and pepper them, then coat with Italian salad dressing; let marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour, then grill or cook in oven.

title: bark candy
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add ingredients and spread out on waxed paper or a cookie sheet.
Cool.
Cut into pieces or break into pieces.

title: christmas festival salad
directions: Mix well, put in mold and congeal.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake per directions on box.
Make 2 layers.
Make pudding, using 3 cups milk.
Add sliced bananas to pudding.
In punch bowl, layer as follows:
1 cake layer, crushed pineapple, pudding with bananas, other cake layer, pie filling and then Cool Whip.
You may also add coconut to bananas and pudding.
Also, you may put chopped nuts on top of Cool Whip, if desired.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break cake into small pieces and cover bottom of oblong dish. Mix vanilla pudding (as directed) and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cake layer.
Refrigerate while mixing next layer.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large saucepan, over medium-high heat, heat broth, chicken, noodles, carrots, onion, celery, dill and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken and noodles are cooked. Serves 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix instant pudding with 1/2 cup orange juice.
Cut up fruit; put together.
Refrigerate.

title: terry's breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place pieces in greased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon sausage over bread and sprinkle cheese over top.
Beat together the eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lo-cal cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over whipped topping and mix.
Add cottage cheese and stir.
Add drained pineapple.
Let set in refrigerator and hour, if desired, but may be eaten immediately.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour milk. Add fruit and nuts; drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Saute peppers and onions until soft in Crisco.
Remove
to bowl.
Cook meat until brown.
Drain meat. Combine all
ingredients
and
put	in a large casserole dish. Top with
favorite
grated cheese.
Heat in oven until bubbly. Freezes well.

title: turnip souffle(better than it sounds!)
directions: Boil turnips in salt water until done; drain and mash.
Add butter, milk, cheese, 2 yolks and seasoning; mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiff egg whites.
Pile lightly into well-greased baking dish. Set in pan of warm water.
Bake at 375° until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate nut zucchini cake
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Set aside.
At high speed of electric mixer, beat eggs until thick.
Gradually add sugar, 1/4 of a cup at a time, beating well.
Add vegetable oil and melted chocolate and continue beating well.
Add vanilla and almond extracts.
At low speed, add sifted flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda mixture.

title: hot orange juice nog
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Beat in orange juice.
Whisk in hot milk.
Serve immediately.

title: egg mcmuffin
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel and set aside. Fry egg and shape the size of the muffin.
When almost done, add cheese slice on top to melt.
Toast muffin.
On one half of muffin, place egg with cheese, then bacon and top half of muffin. Ham can be substituted for bacon.

title: shrimp balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in dry parsley. Refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: haystack candy
directions: In a double boiler over steaming, but not boiling, water, melt morsels until smooth.
Stir in noodles and peanuts until evenly covered.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.
Let harden.

title: sherri's coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan generously with shortening.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Place pieces of dough on top of nuts.
Sprinkle dry butterscotch pudding over rolls.
Mix cinnamon, brown sugar and oleo.
Pour over rolls.
Cover lightly with wax paper or paper towel.
Let stand overnight to rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat first five ingredients for 5 minutes and set aside.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook meat, onions and bell pepper.
Drain off grease.
Add soups, taco sauce and enchilada sauce to meat.
Put layer of Doritos in casserole dish.
Add mixture.
Put cheese on top.
Add a layer of Doritos.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruity sherbet punch
directions: Combine juices and ginger ale in punch bowl. Top with scoops of sherbet. Serve immediately. Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: pasta primavera(microwave or stove-top)
directions: Place zucchini, broccoli, asparagus, mushrooms, beans and peas in steamer inside 3-quart casserole dish.
Cook at 100% power (High) for 5 to 7 minutes or until vegetables are crisp, yet tender.
In the meantime, cook pasta in boiling water on the stovetop for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente.
Drain.
Place oil and garlic in 1 1/2-quart cook-and-measure bowl and cook at 100% power (High), uncovered, for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in red pepper, broth, basil, vegetables and tomatoes.
Arrange hot pasta on large platter and spoon over vegetable mixture.
Garnish with minced parsley and sprinkle with cheese.

title: cauliflower-broccoli medley
directions: Combine vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to vegetables; toss gently.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: parmesan dressing
directions: Mix together and shake.
Contains 10 calories, 35 mg sodium, 0 g fat and 0 cholesterol.

title: greeo casserole
directions: Cut onion and pepper; put in small amount of oil.
Cook, stirring constantly, to keep from burning until it is shiny.
Put hamburger in and stir until color is out.
Cook macaroni in large amount of water.
When macaroni is done, put through colander and mix all ingredients together.
Will keep well in freezer.
When ready to cook, grate cheese on top and cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Less time may be needed for small casserole dish.

title: oven dried beef jerky
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Lay strips in season serve.
Mix rest of ingredients in order given and pour over meat.
Seal. Turn meat over every hour, for a minimum of 4 hours.
Can stand overnight.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Put all ingredients into a large bowl and mix well.
This mixture needs to set in the fridge for at least 2 days to absorb the flavors.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, by hand and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: *applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce just to a boil.
Add gelatin and mix well. Stir in raspberries.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch mold.
Chill until set.
Strawberries and strawberry gelatin may be substituted for raspberries.
May be served as dessert or accompany main meal.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Soften margarine.
Add to peanut butter and sugar.
Mix well. Roll into balls and chill.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add batter.
Spoon peaches over batter.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons of sugar to the juice and add to top of peaches.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Saute chicken in butter.
Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; set aside.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in pan drippings until tender.
Remove from heat; let cool slightly.
Combine vegetables, mushrooms, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, or until chicken tests done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: white chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Microwave chicken until done and dice.
Simmer chicken broth and beans.
Add onion, garlic, chicken and seasonings to broth mixture and slow cook for 2 to 3 hours.
(This is spicy and hot.
Use seasonings to your taste.)

title: sponge cake
directions: Add beaten egg yolks to beaten egg whites.
Gradually add sugar and beat 5 minutes.
Blend in 1 cup flour.
Slowly add 1 cup boiling water.
Blend in remainder of the flour, baking powder and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into ungreased angel food pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cook juice, cornstarch and sugar until thick.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Put in casserole dish and top with crushed crackers. Pour melted butter over top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: oatmeal rhubarb crumble(low-fat, low-salt, low-sugar, high fiber)
directions: Place rhubarb in sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Add water.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix, using oil, eggs and water.
Pour half of batter into pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: date nut cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 2 hours.
Cake must be started in cold oven.
Makes 1 (3 pound) loaf.

title: chicken-bacon nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 24 (1-inch) cubes. Wrap each chicken cube with bacon and secure with a wooden pick. Stir together marmalade and next 4 ingredients in a shallow dish or large Zip-top freezer bag. Add chicken nuggets. Cover or seal and chill 2 hours, turning occasionally. Coat a rack and broiler pan with cooking spray. Place chicken nuggets on rack in broiler pan. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Turn and bake 10 minutes more. Yield: 6 servings.

title: mincemeat nut bread
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and eggs together thoroughly.
Stir in milk and mincemeat.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder then add to mincemeat mixture.
Stir
in walnuts.
Use well greased 9 x 5 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.
When cool wrap in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Blend eggs, soup, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix in broccoli. Top with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco sauce
directions: Chop all ingredients into pan and cook until done.
Can.

title: christmas cake cookies
directions: Pin and cut dates in small chunks.
Cut cherries and pineapple in small pieces. Blanch almonds, chop and toast until golden brown.
Chop Brazil nuts coarsely.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.

title: cheesy pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain and add 1/2 of the bottle of Ranch and 1/2 of the bottle of Italian dressing. Refrigerate. Wash and prepare vegetables. Place in a large bowl. Add cheeses, pepperoni and rotini. Add more dressing, if desired, according to taste. Contents should be slightly creamy.

title: lemon luscious pie
directions: Bake shell before adding filling.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add butter, lemon rind, lemon juice and egg yolks. Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Let cool.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Shortly before serving, remove from freezer and pour 3 quarts of ginger ale over it.
Makes a slushy drink. Serves 50.

title: herbed tomato slices
directions: Slice tomatoes, place in flat dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and shake well. Pour over tomatoes.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight.
At serving time, transfer tomato slices to platter.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter and cinnamon and sprinkle over sliced apples in casserole dish.
Bake until apples are tender at 350°, approximately 1/2 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until done; drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients well.
Garnish with ripe olives.

title: mandarin jewell
directions: Combine jello with hot water (dissolve).
Add nectar; let set for awhile and add pineapple and orange segments.
Refrigerate until set.
Very good served with baked ham dinner.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Heat soy sauce, water, wine, sugar, gingerroot and star anise to boiling in Dutch oven.
Add chicken; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until done, turning chicken and stirring mixture 2-3 times.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In a very large bowl, add Cool Whip, pistachio pudding mix and green food coloring (the color green you like).
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Great as salad or add to pastry shells for a dessert.

title: crispy carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until tender. Drain & slice.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix in onions.
Dot with margarine and cheese.	Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garden spread
directions: Proportions are your own, but start with 2 or 3 tablespoons of any or all the vegetables.
Add to the whipped cream cheese. Flavor with herbs, salt and pepper.
May be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except catsup.
Shape into a loaf (I shape mine into a round loaf to fit crock-pot) and place in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 hours.
Cover top of loaf with catsup, if desired, during last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: grace's tuna patties
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls and flatten out.
Fry in oil.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix together hot water, sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir into lukewarm water mixture, egg and half the flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover tightly with waxed paper or foil.
Store in refrigerator until doubled in bulk or until needed, as long as 5 days.
Shape as desired.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place free from draft until doubled, about 30 minutes. Brush lightly with melted butter.
Bake in moderate oven, 375°, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: In a small bowl,
stir together first 3 ingredients for dressing;
set aside.
Layer
remaining ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Pour on
dressing;
refrigerate at least 4 hours. Toss just before serving.

title: peanut butter reese's cups
directions: Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs, sugar, peanut butter and butter.
Press in greased pan.
Put melted chocolate pieces on top.

title: deer sausage
directions: Grind meat together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Stuff sausage in casings and smoke until done.

title: golden nugget corn strata
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place muffin halves, split side up, in bottom of dish.
Beat eggs. Combine cheeses, green onions, bacon and corn; mix well.
Spoon mixture over muffin halves to completely cover bottom of dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients together, except bananas.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Add bananas before serving.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Blend cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Stir into macaroni and cheese with tuna, mushrooms and 1/2 cup of the grated cheese.
Mix well and fold in the peas.
Put in casserole dish that has been buttered or sprayed with nonstick agent.

title: pineapple beets
directions: Mix
pineapple	juice,	sugar and vinegar.
Slowly stir this mixture
in
the
top part of a double boiler with cornstarch. Cook
until
thickened
and
clear, stirring often to prevent lumping.
Add margarine and crushed pineapple.
Drain beets, slice or cube and add to mixture.

title: mallow whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, 1 cup marshmallows, margarine, juice and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole bowl.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: graham cracker crumb squares
directions: Mix together; spread evenly in an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Cool in pan, makes about 25 cookies.

title: rio grande kidney bean soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves and puree.

title: stuffed mushrooms(great appetizer... melts in your mouth)
directions: Pull out core of mushrooms so button remains.
Soften cream cheese and add fried bacon pieces and remaining ingredients. Stuff mushrooms and bake at 350° for approximately 7 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: guacamole dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients, except bacon; mix well.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes, or until served.
Before serving, stir in bacon or use as garnish.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Add cream cheese, taco seasoning and salsa to cooked hamburg.
Top with 4 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with 1 tablespoon of salt and 2 tablespoons of butter until tender, then add chopped onions, celery, soup and Stove Top contents to this mixture.
Stir all together well and pour in greased casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of the pecans with softened cream cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
When firm, shape into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: chicken prima vera
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken.
Cook and stir until browned.
Add broccoli, peas, carrot and onion; cook and stir until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in broth, basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Makes 4 servings.
Can be doubled.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add applesauce and water, stirring to mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Sift dry ingredients into applesauce mixture.
Stir to blend.
Fold in raisins and drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese-olive balls
directions: Mix first five ingredients altogether and form into small balls.
Insert an olive into the center of each ball, cover the olive completely.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine popcorn and peanuts.
Melt butter.
Stir in sugar and syrup. Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes. Stir often.

title: beef rolls(rouladen)
directions: Beat steaks until thin, sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika and spread with mustard.
Lay a slice of bacon on top of the mustard on each steak.
Place some of the chopped pickles and onions on top of the bacon.
Roll the steak lengthwise and fasten the end with a toothpick or tie it together with a string.
Melt the shortening in a heavy frying pan and brown on all sides.
Add the water and bouillon cube and cover.
Cook over medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Check the pan occasionally to turn the beef rolls and add more water, if needed. Remove the beef rolls and thicken the sauce with flour and season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: linda's italian bean and pasta soup
directions: In Dutch oven pot, put water, beef base, tomatoes, beans, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper; cover and cook on medium heat (checking that beans don't stick) while getting rest of ingredients ready.
In large skillet, brown ground chuck slowly, breaking up with spoon.
When almost done, add onions, carrots, celery and garlic; cook until meat is well browned.
Drain (leave a little fat for flavor).
Add to simmering bean mixture.
At this time, add pasta; cook until pasta is done.
If soup needs liquid, add water.
Serve with crusty hot bread and salad.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallow cream, and bake in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and spread marshmallow cream on cake while hot. Let cool, then frost.

title: fresh fruit salad glaze
directions: Cook ingredients until thick.
Cool, then pour over fruit and mix well to coat fruit.
If using bananas, add when adding the glaze.

title: rabbit jambalaya
directions: Brown rabbit in small amount of oil.
Set browned rabbit aside.
Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and green onions until wilted.
Add water, rice, parsley and rabbit; mix well.
Cover and cook on low heat until rice is done, about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine pretzels and melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes, stirring twice.

title: best-ever chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook beef, onions, green pepper and celery until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir to break up chunks of meat.
Drain kidney beans, reserving liquid.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
If desired, stir in some of the reserved bean liquid to make desired consistency.
Makes 10 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Place spinach in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine soup, onion and cheese in mixing bowl and mix well. Spread the mixture over the spinach. Combine butter and stuffing and put on the top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in bread cubes.
Stir in brown sugar and raisins.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 1 3/4-inch round ovenware cake dish.
Place pan in larger shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water into larger pan 1 inch deep. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and puree.
You may use other frozen fruits and yogurts if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: asparagus-pea casserole
directions: Cut asparagus into 2-inch pieces.
If desired, set aside 6 asparagus pieces and 3 egg slices for garnish.
Layer half each of peas and remaining asparagus in a lightly greased 8-inch square dish.
Top with remaining egg slices and half of cheese.
Combine mushroom soup, sour cream, onion powder and pepper, stirring well. Spoon half of soup mixture over cheese.
Layer remaining asparagus, peas and soup mixture.
Place butter in a custard cup; microwave at High 30 to 45 seconds, or until butter melts.
Add breadcrumbs, stirring well.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over asparagus and peas. Microwave at High 10 minutes, or until thoroughly heated, giving dish a half turn after 5 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese slices and, if desired, garnish with reserved asparagus and egg slices. Cover with aluminum foil; let stand 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix coconut and pecans; spread on bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box; pour mix over the coconut and pecans.
Mix cream cheese, melted butter and sugar; spoon on top of cake mix.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until it passes the toothpick test.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel, pare, boil (until still firm, but a fork can pierce) and drain carrots.
Boil other ingredients together for one minute and pour over boiled carrots.
Marinate overnight.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Mix well. Pack in loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in oleo.
Add soup and chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti until done.
Drain and add to soup mixture along with grated cheese and turkey.
Simmer until turkey is hot and cheese is melted.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed.
Pour in pan over nuts and coconut.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and margarine or butter.
Pour on top of batter.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fluffy pronto pups
directions: Will also need barbecue sticks.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Reserve enough cheese for top.
Cook noodles.
Mix all together.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: connie's italian marinara sauce
directions: Heat oil in a heavy sauce pot.
Add onions, garlic, and parsley and saute several minutes, stirring a few times until garlic is medium to deep brown.
Quickly add cans of sauce and puree and stir, then add sugar, salt and pepper, and basil. Simmer, stirring occasionally for about 20 minutes total. ENJOY!!!

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Heat through.
Top with bacon.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Blend juice, oil, salt and rosemary.
Pour over chicken pieces and let marinate until chicken is thawed (about 6 hours).
Preheat broiler oven.
Broil chicken about 5 minutes on each side.
Baste chicken with marinade.
Serve chicken with long grain and wild rice.

title: honey banana muffins
directions: Put
oil
in bowl first!
Mix all ingredients together, adding soda and baking
powder
last.
Pour into cupcake-lined muffin tins.
(Makes 12 large muffins.) Sesame seed or chopped pecans may be sprinkled on
top
of
batter
before putting in oven.
Bake at 350° for
about
minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Last, add well beaten egg whites, coconut and pecans.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: flan
directions: Caramelize white sugar in a pan.
Coat a baking pan with the sugar syrup.
Beat flan ingredients until smooth and immediately pour over sugar syrup.
Cook in "water bath" at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pina colada
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on lowest speed until smooth.

title: orange cream salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar until light and smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water and cool slightly.
Gradually add to the cheese mixture.
Fold in pineapple and oranges.
Pour into mold. Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.
Delicious!

title: squash casserole
directions: Save 1/4 cup cheese and 2/3 cup cracker crumbs for top.
Mix other ingredients well.
Put in greased baking dish; sprinkle remaining cheese and crackers over top. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Flatten out biscuits in baking dish.
Saute chopped onions in margarine.
Spread over biscuits.
Cover with thickly sliced fresh tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread 3/4 cup mayonnaise on tomatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until it boils.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Scald 2 cups of milk.
Add oleo, sugar and 1 teaspoon of salt to the cooled milk.
Add eggs to mixture, then add yeast which has been dissolved in a little lukewarm water.
Add flour.
Mix altogether and knead well.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Divide into 4 parts and roll in circle. Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon. Raisins may be added.
Roll like jelly roll.
Put in greased bread pans.
Raise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
In a large bowl combine sugar, vinegar and oil. Add beans, onion and pepper.
Stir with rubber spatula.
Keep refrigerated overnight.
Stir again before serving.

title: italian cream liqueur
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and blend very well. Sip cold or add to coffee.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: In large bowl, combine peanut butter, powdered sugar and butter.
Beat until well blended and smooth.
Roll into 1-inch balls and flatten out, making sure sides are smooth.
Place on waxed paper on baking sheet and chill about 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler over simmering water.
Use a toothpick inserted in the center to dip cups into chocolate. Set on waxed paper until hardened.
Use a spoon to drizzle chocolate over top to cover hole.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 100 cups.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Brown in an iron skillet the ground beef, then add all ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into a casserole dish. Cover with 1 can of biscuits.
Put in oven and bake until biscuits are brown.

title: goofy cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Beat the first 3 ingredients together with mixer (will be gooey).
Put in glass dish and pat down.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Mix the last 4 ingredients; pour over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Will look gooey in the middle.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: In saucepan, combine spinach and onion.
Cook according to directions on spinach; drain well.
Press out excess liquid.

title: cake with sauce
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, water and sour cream with mixer until smooth.
Pour into baking pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients with wet ingredients.
Do not beat too much.
Leave lumps.
Dip by spoonfuls onto hot griddle.

title: taco salad
directions: Blend cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Spread in a pie plate.
Spread picante sauce on top; layer with vegetables. Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Peel and dice fresh vegetables.
Boil in about 2 cups water with bouillon cubes for about 15 minutes.
Brown hamburger, onions and pepper; drain.
Add canned vegetables to fresh.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add beef, noodles and Worcestershire.
Cook until noodles are done.
Serve with sandwiches.
Very good on a cold day or reheated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Add sugar and peanut butter.
Gradually add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie shell.
May top with crushed Spanish peanuts.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Overnight is better.

title: winter strawberries
directions: Stir sugar into cranberries and let set at least 2 hours out of refrigerator.
Mix with other ingredients and let stand overnight.
Good as long as it lasts.

title: red beet relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Ladle into clean, hot jars.
Seal at once.
Makes 4 pints.

title: easy sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, horseradish, cream or milk, salt and pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on slices of ham.
Roll ham, jelly roll fashion, and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill.

title: sunkist orange
directions: Mix 1/2 glass Tang orange drink.
Add 1/2 glass Sprite.
Serve over ice.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; stir well and let stand.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine sugars, eggs and oil.
Add sifted ingredients to sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Save broth.
Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup and poppy seed with enough broth to make it kind of soupy. Pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top, covering completely.
Melt the stick of butter and pour over crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Take out 5 to 10 minutes before done and sprinkle with poppy seed. Return to oven for rest of time.

title: lime-nut congealed salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups.
Place on stove and add marshmallows, continuously to heat until the marshmallows are dissolved.
Place Jell-O in bowl.
Pour hot liquid over Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Mix remaining ingredients.

title: not the usual meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place in a meat loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover for the last 1/2 hour.
Chicken gravy can be served with this.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Combine the ingredients in the order listed, mixing them very thoroughly with the mayonnaise.
Refrigerate the sauce and taste after a while for seasoning.
You may need to add more horseradish or mustard, to get a slightly hot edge to the sauce.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.
The sauce can be served on cold boiled shrimp, on tomatoes, lettuce, as a salad dressing or over cold lobster or crab.

title: ever-so-easy fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Generously grease and flour a 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Sift together flour and baking soda; set aside.

title: "aunt mary's pie crust"
directions: Sift flour, white sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco.
Add milk and egg yolk.
Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: coffee squares with chocolate chips
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add brown sugar, cooking oil, warm coffee, vanilla and eggs.
Blend altogether.
Batter is quite thin.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) ungreased pans.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll into balls.
Mix cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Roll balls in sugar mixture.
Drop into greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter, 1/2 cup white sugar and brown sugar until sugar is melted.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Tip out immediately.

title: peanut butter carob cookies
directions: Melt butter over low heat and add honey, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs. After cooling, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon and add them to the cooled mixture. Stir in carob morsels. Drop level measuring tablespoons of mix onto lightly oiled cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: pasties(yields 5 servings)
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and salt.
With a pastry blender, cut shortening into flour until the mixture forms a ball. The pastry will be stickier than regular pie crust.
With floured hands, shape into a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and let rest in refrigerator while preparing filling.

title: pickled carrot salad
directions: Beat the last 6 ingredients together and heat.
Add to carrots while still hot.
Add sliced green pepper, onion and salt to taste.
Cool; let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Keeps a long time.
Delicious.

title: pasta with scallops and bacon lardons
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil and 2 tablespoons olive oil. Using remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil in large skillet over medium heat, add bacon and saute until crisp.
Remove bacon with slotted spoon and keep warm.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup of bacon fat.
Add scallops; cook over medium heat until they are no longer opaque.
Remove scallops.
Discard all remaining fat.
Add heavy cream and reduce by 1/3.
Put pasta in boiling water; cook until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain in a colander.
While pasta is cooking, add bacon, scallops and thyme to the cream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Warm through over medium heat. Divide sauce among 4 dinner plates and place cooked pasta over sauce.

title: dogs in a sweater
directions: Separate dough.
Roll each piece into a 15-inch rope.
Insert sticks into hot dogs lengthwise.
Starting at one end, wrap dough in a spiral around hot dog.
Pinch ends to seal.
Place 1-inch apart on a baking sheet that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve with toppings of your choice.
Serves 8.

title: ginger plum spareribs
directions: In saucepan, stir together preserves, corn syrup, soy sauce, green onions, garlic and ginger.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 5 minutes.
Remove 1 cup; set aside.

title: counterfeit chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a buttered casserole and bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Season fryer with salt and broil on both sides until brown. In saucepan, mix the chicken broth, soup and enough water to cover the chicken in a baking dish.
Put all in baking dish and season to taste.
Put in 350° oven for 30 minutes, then top with biscuits and bake until biscuits are done.

title: cola chicken(low calorie)
directions: Cut up chicken.
Pour ketchup and diet drink over it.
Cook until done in slow cooker or pressure cooker.
There are 283 calories.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in 2 quarts of boiling water and 1 tablespoon olive oil approximately 20 minutes.
Rinse in cold water and set aside.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Brown meat with onions and bell pepper; drain and let cool. Crumble cornbread and add to meat mixture.
Add green onion, parsley and soups.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese apples
directions: Mix and let set until clear.
Add flour and stir.
Pour apples into 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in two layers.
Mix pudding as directed. Have fruits chilled. Beginning with cake in bottom of bowl, spoon pudding over cake with half mixture.
Spoon half of each item near the glass side of the bowl in layers, then spread one container of Cool Whip over that.
Start over.
It is both beautiful and delicious!
Keep refrigerated.

title: oven stew
directions: Put meat in bottom of roaster.
Add potatoes, carrots, onions and celery (cut in chunks).
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour tomatoes over all.
Cover; cook in 250° oven.
Do not open lid for 4 hours.

title: creamy chicken soup
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan; blend in flour.
Stir in chicken broth, milk, and cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and boiling.
Add chicken and pepper; return to a boil.
Serve immediately.

title: peppered steak
directions: Brown meats and onions in skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add granulated garlic and a good measure of oregano; add some sweet basil; add either Hunt's special sauce or puree, home canned tomatoes and enough water to make soupy.
Cook down to a sauce, adding bell pepper to taste; approximately 10 minutes before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place 1/3 of potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Place 1/3 of onion on top of potatoes.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/3 of this mixture on top of onion.
Repeat layers twice.
Pour hot milk and chicken broth over all.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 5 to 6. A 1/2 cup serving contains 73 calories and 0.1 gram of fat.

title: black beans dinner
directions: Soak black beans in water overnight, drain.
Add 8 cups of fresh water with salt and cook over low heat until beans are tender.

title: seedy bread sticks
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; cut each in half.
Roll and shape each half into 5-inch stick.
In shallow dish combine cereal and salt.
Pour milk into small bowl.
Dip each stick into milk; roll in cereal mixture to coat.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle lightly with sesame or poppy seed.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 20 snacks.

title: string beans
directions: Heat oil in shallow baking pan at 400°; add string beans, chopped onion and salt.
Toss and turn ingredients; cook 10 minutes or until done.
You can make a
lot or a little; for smaller quantities, you can do this in a frying pan on a burner.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake half of it in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk and margarine. Spread half of caramel mixture over baked cake.
Sprinkle half of chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour in rest of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread rest of caramel as frosting. Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips and pecans.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies(no cholesterol)
directions: Sift
together	the
flour,
baking
soda and cinnamon. Stir in the oats.
Combine egg whites, brown sugar, oil, milk, vanilla and
raisins and add to flour mixture.
Drop batter a teaspoon
at a time onto an oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for
to 15 minutes, depending on texture desired.
Shorter baking time results in a chewy soft cookie, the longer time is a crisp one. Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Cook 5 to 6 hours in crock-pot.

title: warm beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Let cool.
Take off peel.
Grate beets as for Borsch.
Melt butter; add grated beets, salt, sugar and lemon juice.

title: baked fish parmesan
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, bouillon and seasonings.
Cut fish in serving-size pieces.
Dip fish in melted butter, turning to coat both sides.
Let excess butter drain off, then dip fish into seasoned crumbs, coating well. Place fish on lightly buttered shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle fish with any remaining butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Heat milks.
Combine ingredients.
Sprinkle some cinnamon on top.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: stir-fried pineapple rice
directions: In small bowl, combine soy and oyster sauces.
Over high heat, heat wok or large heavy skillet (preferably nonstick) until drop of water evaporates on contact.
Add sesame oil; heat about 10 seconds.
Add garlic and ginger; stir-fry about 10 seconds.
Add sake or broth, bell pepper, mushrooms and pineapple; stir-fry until peppers are crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Cream margarine, 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour. Spread dough in bottom and on sides of 9-inch spring-form pan. Combine softened cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar; mix well.
Blend in egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into pastry lined pan.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Put eggs in a medium bowl.
Dip each chicken breast in eggs until well coated.

title: sunny silver pie
directions: Soak gelatin in water; beat egg yolks until light, add juice and grated rind of lemon and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Place this in a double boiler and cook, stirring all the time until smooth.
Add gelatin and cook 2 minutes more. Remove from heat and add stiffly beaten egg whites to which the other 1/2 cup of sugar has been added.
Fill a 9 inch baked pie shell with mixture.
Refrigerate at least three hours
before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: milky way wonder cake
directions: Melt bars and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan over low heat.

Cream remaining butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk. Stir until smooth. Add melted candy; mix well. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan (10-inch) at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done when tested with a toothpick. Cool a few minutes; remove from pan.
Frost with a buttercream frosting or as desired.

title: pig licking good cake
directions: Mix for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice; drain fruits.
Add fruits and nuts; whip cream until thickens.
Pour all ingredients in mold and freeze for 3 to 12 hours.
Serve frozen; slices real well.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of pan.
Spoon salsa on next, top with shredded Mexican cheese.
Place in preheated 350 - 375 oven until cheese melts and bubbles, 10 - 15 minutes.
Serve with corn chips scoops.

title: brownies
directions: In bowl, combine brown sugar, butter and maple flavoring. Beat in eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to egg mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.)
Yields 16 brownies.

title: planter's club corn pudding
directions: Mix all
ingredients and cook at 400° about 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 5.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Whip cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise together.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped Dream Whip. Freeze.
Thaw about 30 minutes before serving.

title: party mix
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large roasting pan. Combine oil, brown sugar, Worcestershire and garlic salt.
Pour over first 6 ingredients and toss to coat.
Bake in oven at 250 degrees for 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: hot cranberry-apple drink
directions: Put all ingredients in a large crock-pot and let simmer.
Great for holiday gatherings and sleigh-riding parties.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes, apple and raisins in a 9 x 13-inch buttered metal pan.
Heat milk, sugar and margarine until margarine is melted.
Beat eggs well in a large bowl. Add hot milk slowly to eggs; mix well. Pour over
bread cubes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with Rum Sauce.

title: swiss vegetable medley(ready to bake in 5 minutes)
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 of cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish and bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mrs. laura's dump cake
directions: Spoon pie filling into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over top.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Drizzle butter over top. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and arrange in 7 x 11-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Top with chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine soup, sour cream and lemon juice.
Mix well and pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian delight
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in a large skillet.
Remove excess fat, add corn, olives, mushrooms and tomato sauce; simmer for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soups, chicken, vegetables and broth together and pour in a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix flour, milk, margarine and baking powder together and pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into a greased and sugared (not floured) pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: microwave turtles
directions: Combine half the chocolate chips and 1/2 the shortening in glass bowl.
Microwave on Medium until melted.
Mix well.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square dish.
Chill for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed pears
directions: Drain pears; place sliced side up on platter.
Drain pineapple. Mix cream cheese, pineapple and nuts together; works best when cheese is at room temperature.
Spoon into pears; top with cherry.

title: italian hamburger casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
In blender, combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Stir in green onions.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer cooked noodles, cream cheese mixture, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake for about 1 hour until bubbly.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheese whole wheat short pastry tartlet shells
directions: Combine flour, cheese, dry mustard, paprika and ground red pepper in large mixing bowl.
Add butter and blend with fingertips until mixture resembles coarse meal.

Add egg yolk and water mixture and blend well, working dough as little as possible and adding more water 1 tablespoon at a time if dough is too dry. Turn dough out onto unfloured work surface and quickly form into ball.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Add diced green onions, cut-up dried beef and add 1 teaspoon of Accent.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in ball.
Shape and cover with pecans. Refrigerate until ready to serve with crackers.

title: grandma o's cookies
directions: Place by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and save 1/4 cup of the juice. Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of hot water.
Stir in cranberries and crushed pineapple.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture in a bowl and leave at room temperature; set the other 1/2 in the refrigerator until firm.
In a separate bowl, mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise, reserved pineapple juice, and chopped pecans.
Spread mixture over chilled gelatin.
Place in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Pour the room temperature gelatin over the top of the cream cheese layer and refrigerator until set.

title: cucumber dill appetizers
directions: Mix Italian dressing into softened cream cheese.
Spread on bread. Top with one thinly sliced cucumber.
Sprinkle dill on top.

title: sue's low-fat yogurt pie
directions: Mix the yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Mix well and put into graham cracker crust.
Top with same fruit used in yogurt.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: tasty tomato soup(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a quart measure container. Microwave on High, uncovered, for 5 to 6 minutes or until it begins to boil.
Remove bay leaf and clove; serve.
Two to three servings.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: In glass bowl mix sugar, salt and corn starch.
Add 1/2 c. milk to beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
Then add remainder of milk. Add egg and milk mixture to dry ingredients. Place in the microwave and cook on high for 5 minutes and 50 seconds, stirring 2 or 3 times until thick.
In large oven-safe bowl, put a layer of wafers, then bananas and then a layer of pudding mix. Then another layer of wafers, then bananas and then pudding.
Beat egg whites until frothy with 1/4 c. sugar and top pudding.
Brown in oven.

title: sunday special casserole
directions: Spread raw ground beef in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle chopped onion over meat.
Spread undiluted soup on top of onions.
Top soup with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: spring salad
directions: Cook the noodles for 12 minutes and drain.
Add the celery and onion.
Dressing is made with the rest of the ingredients.
Mix with a wire whisk.
Pour the dressing over the noodles and refrigerate all night.

title: musemandeln(tiny almonds)
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add melted butter and blend.
Add flour and baking powder which have been sifted together.
Blend well.
Add rum.

title: rice chantilly
directions: Combine rice, sour cream, salt, Tabasco and 1/2 cup cheese. Spoon into
a buttered, shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all together very well and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes, or until pie is done. Touch the top with your fingers to make sure it's firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole(microwave)
directions: Lay Stove Top stuffing crumbs in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Top with melted butter and hot water.
Break boiled cooked chicken up in pieces and layer over stuffing.
Put frozen broccoli in a pan of hot water for five minutes, just enough to thaw.
Drain and layer over chicken.
Mix soup and one cup of milk together and pour over casserole.
Top with shredded cheese and bread crumbs. Bake in microwave for 20 minutes.

title: picadillo
directions: Brown meat.
Add everything else and bring to boil.
Let simmer for several hours.
Good served with Doritos.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Combine hot sauce, vinegar and butter.
Cook until butter melts.
Add chicken wings.
Cook until wings are done.
Remove from heat.
Let wings soak for 1 to 2 hours.
Take wings from sauce.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper (add more or less pepper for desired taste).
Bake on 350° until wings brown.
Serve using Blue cheese dressing as a dip.

title: shortbread sparkler buds
directions: Cream butter with sugar until fluffy.
Blend in flour gradually, then beat at medium speed for 5 minutes, or knead with hands until satin-smooth.
Pat out to a rectangle (9 x 6-inch) on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Chill several hours or until dough is firm enough to hold its shape when cut (overnight is better).
Cut into rounds with a floured 1-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle generously with decorating sugar.
Chill 30 minutes before baking.
Pat out trimmings to 3/4-inch thick. Chill and cut, following earlier instructions.
Bake at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until cookies are firm in center and lightly golden around edges.
Remove; cool completely on wire racks.

title: prawns ala manilena
directions: Peel and clean prawns and cut in halves lengthwise.
Roll in cornstarch to coat lightly.
Heat oil in skillet or wok and fry over high heat.
Fry prawns very quickly until crisp.
Drain and set aside.

title: raspberry-dijon sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients until hot.
Serve with chicken or fish. Makes 1 cup sauce.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Process at high speed until smooth.
Use in any recipe calling for the commercially sold sweetened condensed milk.
Makes 1 1/4 cups (10 ounces) and contains 1205 calories.

title: wine roast
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brush meat with olive oil.
Rub salt and pepper over meat.
Pour wine over meat.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into balls.

title: swedish cinnamon sticks
directions: Combine butter, margarine and sugar.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Roll small amounts in 2-inch sticks.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
When done, roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: sugarless oatmeal date cookies
directions: Combine dates and water in saucepan.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes to absorb moisture.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet from teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cookies are brown.
Yields 36 cookies.

title: swedish pineapple dump cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together until blended. Add other 3 ingredients and mix again. This is why it is called a dump cake; just dump everything in at once. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch METAL pan or use 2 layer cake pans.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Mix the taco seasoning with water into the browned turkey or beef.
In baking dish, layer in the following order: seasoned meat, beans, picante sauce, 1 cup cheese, sour cream, green taco sauce and 1 cup cheese. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Dip with corn or tortilla chips.

title: elephant bread
directions: Evening:
Dissolve baking soda with 1/4 cup of water.
Pour over oatmeal, raisins, brown sugar and oil.
Moisten these ingredients with hot water to cover (approximately 2 1/2 cups) and let stand overnight.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1/4 to 3/4 cup of mix to 1 cup of boiling mug of water.

title: beef chowder
directions: Brown beef and pour off any grease.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook 15 minutes in pressure cooker and let steam come down on its own.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice and jello on stove, bring to a boil. Let cool to room temperature (can put pan in ice water to cool). Add other ingredients; stir.
Pour into 9x13 pan and refrigerate until chilled.

title: springtime lime salad
directions: Beat milk until firm.
Add cream cheese, a little at a time, beating well.
Cook pineapple and sugar; boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add dry jello.
Mix all ingredients and pour in mold.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Braise pork chops that have been pounded with rosemary on top. In a blender, combine orange juice, vinegar, ginger and garlic; mix well.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Place peaches and juice in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place dry cake mix on top of peaches, then put margarine and pecans on top.
Put in oven at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Can serve with Cool Whip.

title: grilled marinated salmon
directions: Mix all.
Marinate salmon fillets for 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Cook on grill, skin side down, until the salmon flakes.
Do not turn.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: pigs in the blanket
directions: Open dinner rolls and let set at room temperature until thawed.
Cut 5 wieners into 4 pieces each.
Ope each roll and place 1 piece of wiener in middle of roll.
Fold over and seal tight.
Place in greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown at 325° to 350°.
Makes 20 pigs in blanket.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, using an electric mixer.
Chill mixture. This is a good dip for celery, cauliflower, carrots, cucumbers, etc.

title: czech kolaches
directions: Mix 1/2 cup milk, yeast, 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Let this mixture stand for 10 minutes.
Cream shortening, egg yolks, sugar, salt and milk.
Add this to first mixture.
Add the flour and knead well.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine ingredients for filling.
Put in unbaked crust and bake in 350° oven until firm.

title: armadillo in sour cream sauce
directions: Mix wine, oil, garlic powder and onion.
Cut up armadillo and marinate in the refrigerator overnight.
Melt butter in a large skillet and brown the meat.
Pour in the marinade and bring to a boil.
Stir in spices, cover and simmer until meat is tender (1 to 2 hours).
Remove from heat and place armadillo pieces on a platter.
Mix cornstarch with a little water to form a paste and add to the liquid in the skillet.
Add the sour cream.
Heat without boiling until sauce has thickened.
Add the meat pieces and continue heating for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sesame pan bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt and 1 stick butter.
Add eggs and flour.
Stir together.
Let rise 1 hour in warm place.
Stir down and pour into oblong baking pan or 2 loaf pans.
Cover with 1/2 stick melted butter; spread sesame seed on top.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Can be reheated in foil in moderate oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Measure berries before grinding.
Food processor is great. Combine Jell-O, hot water and sugar.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into Jell-O mold.

title: old fashioned swedish waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron.
Beat egg whites until firm; let stand.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add egg yolks, melted butter, vanilla and 2/3 of the milk; beat until smooth.
Add remaining milk. Carefully add beaten egg whites to mixture just before baking. Bake to golden brown.
Cool waffles on rack for crispness.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes. Add coconut and blend again for 1 minute.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh asparagus soup
directions: Wash and remove tips from asparagus.
Simmer the tips (covered) until tender in small amount of water.
Cut the stalks into pieces and place in large saucepan.
Add water, bouillon cubes, onion and celery.
Simmer, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Pour into blender and blend until mushy.
Melt in top of double boiler:
butter and flour; slowly add cream.
Add asparagus stock.
Heat soup, adding asparagus tips, seasoning before serving.
Pass the croutons please.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: two crust pie
directions: Prepare pie crusts according to package directions for two crust pie.
Mix pie filling, cranberry sauce and cornstarch.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in top. Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Complete baking (according to package directions) at 325° until it bubbles.

title: artichoke and mushroom soup
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour; cook slowly for 2 minutes.
Slowly add broth and half and half.
Stir with whisk over low heat to thicken.
Stir in artichokes and seasonings.

title: the big dipper
directions: Mix all ingredients and microwave or heat in saucepan until melted and mixed.
Serve warm with tortilla chips, toasted French bread or veggie dippers.

title: pumpkin apple bread(method:  dutch oven)
directions: Mix ingredients, dry first, then eggs, oil, pumpkin and then the apples.
Bake in Dutch oven.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Saute vegetables in 1/2 stick butter.
Make roux of flour and 1 stick butter.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add to vegetables. Add seasonings, chicken, crab and chicken stock.
Cook, covered, slowly for 45 minutes.
Stir often.
Add shrimp, okra and parsley. Let cook for 15 minutes.
Let sit on stove; lid on, burner off, until ready to serve, at least one hour.
Heat before serving. Taste for salt.
Ladle over rice in individual bowls.
Freezes well!!

title: fresh berry pie
directions: Combine cold water, sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Mixture should clear and become thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin powder.
Allow to cool to room temperature.
Fill the baked pie crust with berries.
Pour gelatin mixture over berries and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla yogurt if desired.
Serves 8.

title: kraut vegetable salad
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.

title: cowboy hats
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes accordingly.
Place bologna on a plate.
Use a small ice cream dipper to place a scoop of potatoes on the bologna.
Top with a slice of cheese.
Place plate in microwave for 2 minutes.

title: delicious marinade for london broil
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour over meat.
Marinate for several hours.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sugar, flour, eggs, soda, pineapple and its juice in a mixing bowl. Add 1/2 cup nuts and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and butter. Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Cool. Dissolve jello in boiling juice; add fruit. Let set until it begins to gel. Mix sugar with cheese. Add the whipped topping. Pour cheese mixture over pretzels. When set, pour jello over this.

title: moms cream of chicken
directions: Cut chicken into fryer pieces.
Whisk eggs together.
Roll chicken into egg mixture.
Then into flour.
Fry in hot oil, add salt,
pepper and garlic powder to your liking.
When browned, place in baking dish and pour the cream of chicken soup with milk added over the chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese with everything, except beef.
Put beef in blender.
Add half of beef to cheese mixture.
Roll cheese ball in remaining beef.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat; add 1 3/4 cups peanut butter; blend well.
Add cereal, stirring to coat. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt chips and 3/4 cup peanut butter together until smooth.
Spread over cereal mixture. Cool and cut into squares.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Cut veal into 6 serving-sized pieces, pound until thin. Dredge with seasoned flour.
Dip into egg, coat with mixture of crumbs and cheese.
Brown veal in hot oil in large heavy skillet. As pieces brown, place in shallow (13 x 9-inch) baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over veal; top with cheese.
Set in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and vanilla.
Add the remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 4 cups hot water; cool.
Add pineapple and blueberry filling.
Pour into 2 small dishes or 1 (9 x 13-inch) dish and refrigerate.
Soften cream cheese; mix with sour cream, sugar, dash of vanilla and chopped nuts.
After Jell-O has congealed, spread on top.
Serves 16.

title: quick and easy potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; cut up in 1/4 to 1/2-inch chunks or slices. Place cut potatoes in plastic bag and pour in dry soup mix.
Shake up potatoes until coated with soup mix.
Spray casserole dish with Pam or lightly grease.
Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Place bacon over potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter or margarine and evaporated milk in a large pan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until ingredients melt.
Continue cooking to soft ball stage (235° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; quickly stir in marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Pour into two 8 x 8 x 2-inch square, greased pans.
Cut into squares when cold.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: snoopy snacks
directions: Melt the bits in a saucepan over hot water.
When bits are melted, stir in peanut butter and any of the following: nuts, coconut, raisins, Chinese noodles or cereal.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: aunt em's wild rice
directions: Combine wild rice and broth.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Fry celery and onion in butter until transparent.
When rice is cool and fluffy, mix with celery and onion; put in a casserole with mushroom pieces and juice.
Cover with mushroom soup and sprinkle on almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add a little water if it becomes dry.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put sharp cheese into food processor and grate.
Empty into a large bowl.
Put onion and pepper into processor and chop.
Add last 3 ingredients to cheese, mix well and roll into ball.
Then roll ball into pecans.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: shaker potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a casserole dish.
Spread potatoes in dish.
Press cheese into potatoes.
Sprinkle onion on top. Sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan and pepper over mixture.
Top all with small dots of butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coquito
directions: Combine the coconut milk and the sugar in a saucepan; scald over medium heat. Beat the egg yolks with the vanilla. Beat in 1/2 cup of the scalded mixture into the egg yolks. Then whisk all the egg yolk mixture into the scalded mixture. Stirring mixture constantly, cook over low heat until mixture reaches a temperature of 160°F (71°C). The mixture should be thick enough to coat the back of a spoon. DO NOT BOIL. Strain the eggnog into a bowl. Stir in the rum and let cool to room temperature. Place plastic wrap on the surface and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: ginger mandarin frosting
directions: Stir ginger preserves and marmalade together until soft.
Split cake into 2 layers.
Spread half of this mixture over bottom layer of split cake.
Beat cream with sugar and vanilla until stiff. Spread half of cream over ginger and marmalade mixture, sprinkle with nuts.
Put on top layer, repeat ginger, cream and nut layer.

title: peach pizza
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Pat out like pizza crust. Cook for 30 minutes at 300°. Let cool.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured surface, knead lightly 3 or 4 times and roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together, but do not beat.
Add berries last.
Fill muffin tins, lined to 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pound this into meat.
Cut into small pieces.
Brown in fat or oil.
Place other ingredients on meat.
Cover with lid.
Simmer on stove slowly.
Stir occasionally.
Do not let boil dry.
Cook at least an hour.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground chuck. Drain off the grease. Add chili, refried beans, and cheese. Mix well. Sprinkle some cheese on top. Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes. Eat with tortilla chips or put inside soft taco shell for a beef and bean taco.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Butter bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Put mixture in pan.
Salt and pepper raw chicken and lay over mixture.
Cut up 1 stick of butter and lay on top of chicken. Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350 for 2 hours.

title: frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool completely.
In separate

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook vegetables in oil until tender (approximately 10 minutes).
Add other ingredients, except shrimp, and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 15 minutes.

title: wet chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil the water, cocoa, oil and margarine.
Add this mixture to the flour and sugar which has been mixed together. Then add vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix until smooth.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and pumpkin pie spice in an ungreased 8-inch square pan with a fork.
Add butter and stir until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside 1/2 cup crumbs.

title: sweet potato gypsy soup(for health nuts)
directions: Saute sweet potatoes, onions, celery and garlic in olive oil. Add seasonings; simmer.
Add chickpeas, tomatoes, sweet pepper, water and Bragg; simmer a tad more.
Serve.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Brown beef.
Add salad dressing, spaghetti sauce and noodles. Heat on medium, stirring occasionally. Top with cheese.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Cube potatoes into small chunks.
Place in large pot along with broth, bacon, onions, parsley, cloves and peppercorns.
Cook for 1 hour or more until broth is cooked down and thickened adequately.
Some of the potato chunks can be removed, mashed and returned to pot, if desired.
Add the milk, butter and sour cream mixture and stir well.
Cook until warm and of desired thickness. Salt to taste.
Add cream to entire pot before serving.
Remove peppercorns and cloves.
Garnish with grated cheese, bacon bits and green onion tops (sliced thin).

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine 1 stick of margarine (melted), potatoes, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with corn flakes.
Pour 1/2 stick of melted margarine over flakes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Stir and add first four ingredients to large pot.
Cook and stir on medium heat until meat is white (do not brown meat).
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Put on simmer for 4 hours. Serve over spaghetti with Parmesan cheese.
The soda cuts acid in tomatoes and causes foam for a while.

title: apple brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and salt, then add the egg and sugar; beat well.
Stir in remaining ingredients; blend well.

title: caribbean lamb salad
directions: With long, sharp knife, halve pineapple lengthwise. (Pineapple shells will be used as bowls; handle carefully.)
Cut out core and discard.
Cut flesh into cubes or tidbits.
In a large bowl, combine lamb, pineapple, orzo, celery, raisins, cashews and scallions; mix well.
In small bowl, blend mayonnaise, mustard, curry and lemon juice.
Stir dressing into salad; toss to mix and coat.
Fill pineapple; sprinkle with coconut.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch for pennies
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and pineapple juice in a punch bowl.
Add water and stir well.
Add ginger ale and ice when ready to serve. A great crowd pleaser!

title: magic cookie bars(club member: renee evans)
directions: Pour melted butter onto the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over crumbs.
Scatter chocolate chips over nuts.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over chocolate pieces.
Pour milk evenly over coconut.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
