title: marbled chocolate bars
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions.
Pour into a greased 15 in. x 10 in. x 1 in. baking pan.
In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in 1/4 c. chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoons over batter.
Cut through batter with a knife to swirl the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in microwave.
Mix fudge brownie mix, remaining evaporated milk and margarine.
Pour 1/2 batter in glass baking dish.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Stir gelatin into whipped topping until smooth.
Add drained oranges, undrained pineapple, orange juice concentrate, marshmallows and nuts if desired.
Stir; cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Serves 8.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs on all sides.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add sauce and bake one hour in a covered pan at 350°.
Good served with rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients.
Alternate dry ingredients with grated zucchini into creamed mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour, in greased
and floured loaf pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone; save broth.
Brown Rice-A-Roni as instructed on box.
After browned, spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir in chicken and seasonings.
Cover with broth.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix ingredients thoroughly. Pour into 2 (8-inch) round cake pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until cake tests done. When cake is cool, frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix coffee and sugar together and dissolve in boiling water; let cool.
Skim foam off the top, add vanilla bean pieces and almost the fifth of brandy.
Bottle and cork.
Do not open for 30 days.

title: mincemeat coffee cake
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup milk.
Add sugar, butter, eggs, salt, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, mace, 2 1/2 cups flour and the remaining milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down; let rest 10 minutes.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface.
Roll into a 16 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread mincemeat to within 1-inch of edges. Roll up from one long side.
Pinch seams; join and seal ends to form a circle.
Place in a greased 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Cover and let rise until nearly doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing to a wire rack.
Just before serving, dust with confectioners sugar.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt butter in large pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until marshmallows are melted.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add rice cereal. Stir until well coated.
Pour in buttered pan and press.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: In the 1/3 cup milk, melt cheese, then add all remaining ingredients except for mayonnaise.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes and then add mayonnaise.
Let cool before serving.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix biscuit pieces in mixture.
Place in greased pan. Pour remaining mixture into a cup and add enough sugar to make 1 cup.
Add melted margarine to this and mix.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg yolks and poppy seed. Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Add alternately with flour.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Over cherries put sugar.
Let stand while you make batter as follows:
Cream butter with 1/2 cup sugar, then add flour with baking powder and salt.
Add sweet milk and stir well. Pour batter into buttered baking dish.
Add cherries and cover with boiling water.
The batter will come to top while baking at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can also use blackberries in this recipe.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla flavoring.
Place small spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook until thick.
Pressure cook for 25 minutes for pint jars and 30 minutes for quart jars at 10 pounds.
To each quart add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar.

title: kim knapp's buster-bar ice cream cake
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread 1/2 gallon ice cream over chilled crust.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts.

title: chicken wings with mushrooms
directions: Disjoint wings.
Soak mushrooms in 1 1/2 cups water.
Cut green pepper into bite size.
Fry wings in oil.
Remove mushrooms from water.
Add shoyu and sugar to mushroom water.
Slice mushrooms and put on wings.
Add green pepper.
Pour sauce and simmer.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (save some cracker crumbs for top).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Use a rolling pin to flatten each slice of bread.
Mix cheese and egg in mixing bowl and spread evenly over bread and edges. Place asparagus on bread.
Roll up and secure with 3 toothpicks. Dip in melted butter.
Place on baking sheet and freeze. Partially thaw rolls and cut each roll into 3 equal parts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yield: 60 bites.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix thoroughly in order given and refrigerate.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; roll biscuit quarters in the mixture.
Place in buttered pan.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar and 1 stick melted butter.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: meat loaf cups
directions: Mix ingredients lightly in bowl.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings (two per person).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up baked chicken breasts and put in dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream, carrots and onion; pour over chicken. Mix oleo with stuffing mix and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Mix sauce ingredients in bowl.
If too thick add vinegar; if too watery, add ketchup.
Dip ribs in sauce and marinate overnight or all day.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for additional 15 to 25 minutes.
If no sauce left, make 1/2 sauce recipe and spoon over ribs.
When done, will look barbecued and thick with glaze.

title: wedding cake cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, almond extract and water.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add pecans and mix.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Beat concentrated juice in mixer bowl about 30 seconds.
Blend in ice cream.
Fold in Cool Whip until smooth.
Freeze until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm or overnight.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: leftovers delight
directions: Cook onion in margarine in skillet until tender.
Add meat, cooked rice and soup.
Combine thoroughly.
May add a little milk for moisture.
Cover and simmer over very low heat about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serves four to five.

title: low calorie salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O; stir until Jell-O is evenly spread.
Drain juice from pineapple and orange sections, then stir into cottage cheese and Cool Whip mixture. Chill.
Keep in refrigerator.
Very good as a low calorie salad.

title: graham cracker sweets
directions: Break graham crackers into fourths and place on rimmed cookie tray (ungreased).
Melt butter, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop mixture onto crackers and spread.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a jar with a tight lid.
Shake well. Reshake with every use.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces almond bark in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries and sprinkle with coconut.
Melt remaining 2 ounces of almond bark.
Stir until smooth.
Drizzle over coconut.
Chill until firm.
Store at room temperature.
For smaller pizzas, shape on wax paper lined cookie sheet.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Mix butter, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, salt, pepper
and
sugar
for sauce.
Heat until well blended. Place chicken
in
covered
casserole
or wrap in foil.
Brush sauce over chicken and brown under broiler.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon pies
directions: Blend together whipped topping and milk. Then add in lemon juice. Spoon into pie crusts and chill until set.

title: chili-con casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add chili seasoning, tomato soup and water.
Add corn and cook about 10 minutes.

title: easy popcorn balls
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until melted.
Pour over popcorn. Make into balls.
Good and easy.

title: cheese cake
directions: Chill the jello and hot water until syrupy. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons jello to the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla to whip. Fold together. Put into Graham Cracker Crust. Sprinkle few crumbs on top. Chill.

title: janie's coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until looks like whip cream.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add alternately flour and milk.
Blend well using electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans at 350° until brown or a tester comes out clear.
Cool on a wire rack until cold.
Ice with white frosting.

title: sausages, peppers, mushrooms
directions: Fork sausages and put in pan in oven at 350°.
Bake until brown and almost done.
Remove most of fat.
Put peppers, onions and mushrooms in pan and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sausages which have been cut into pieces.
Mix together and add tomato sauce plus 1 can of water.
Mix well.
Cook about 1/2 hour until tender. Good over rice or just as a sandwich.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine sauces and water.
Stir 1/2 cup into beef along with chilies, half of cheese and half of onions.
Mix well.
Pour half of remaining sauce mixture on bottom of 10-inch round or 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Stuff cooked shells with beef mixture.
Arrange in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
(Hot chilies and/or picante sauce can be used for a spicier dish.)

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar, Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring to milk.
Sift flour; measure and add baking powder and sift again.
Add enough flour (a couple of spoonfuls) to nuts to coat.
Add remaining flour and milk, a little at a time. Stir in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: corn sticks
directions: Cook onion in shortening, until yellowed.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg and corn.
Add onion and mix well.
Fill greased corn stick pans 2/3 full.
Bake in a hot 450° oven until brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, muffin mix last.
Pour into shallow greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine to room temperature.
Mix together with chopped onions.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight until can form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: coconut pecan rolls
directions: Mix coconut, pecans, powdered sugar, melted butter and vanilla.
Roll into balls.
Place on wax paper and chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, add to rest of ingredients and mix well; place into greased casserole (11 x 13-inch).
Cook 60 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken. Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle over chicken/sour cream mix.
Sprinkle poppy seed over.
Melt butter and pour over all.
Bake 30 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Lightly mix drained fruit together.
In separate bowl, fold sour cream into whipped cream.
Fold dressing and fruit together. Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 12.
Can be made several hours ahead, but not frozen.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Stiffly whip the cream.
Rinse and cap the strawberries; blot dry on paper towels.
Slice strawberries and sprinkle with sugar. (If strawberries are sweet, no sugar is required.)
Divide the strawberries and put between cake layers.
(Do not put strawberries on top or they may bleed into cream.)
Spread whipped cream over the cake.
Cut and serve.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add onion and cook until softened. Add the can of soup and sour cream and stir well.
Add garlic powder, Worcestershire and salt and pepper.
Simmer over medium to low heat for 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, peel onions and cut into 1/4 inch rings. Arrange in layers, sprinkling salt on each layer.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Add cucumbers and onions and simmer 10 minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes about 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, sprayed with Pam or greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: bishop's cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts, dates and cherries.
Fold into egg mixture being sure it is mixed well so there are no dry spots.
Pour into a loaf pan that has been greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
Cool on rack before turning out. Keep tightly wrapped as it dries out rather quickly.
A dip of vanilla ice cream enhances the taste.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix the first six ingredients; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top and drizzle melted butter on flakes.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly just until moistened.
Fold in blueberry mixture. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven about 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour, cream, milk and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shredded potato and ham pie
directions: In a bowl combine eggs, vegetables, ham, 1 cup cheese, milk and onion.
Set aside.
Combine shredded potatoes and the 1/2 cup shredded cheese, press into bottom and sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Pour filling into potato-lined pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
(Makes 6 servings.)

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in order given, cutting in shortening as you normally would for biscuits.
Stir in buttermilk.
Also water with yeast in it.
Blend thoroughly and the dough is ready to be refrigerated in large bowl or made into biscuits.
When ready to work dough, turn onto a floured board and knead lightly as for regular biscuits. Roll out, cut and place on greased pan.
Let rise slightly if cold.
Bake at 400°.
Dough can be refrigerated up to 3 days.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine softened butter and sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to egg, sugar and butter.
Fold in mashed banana.
Bake in muffin tins (any size) at 350° for 20 minutes in small tins or 25 minutes in big tins.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak with the mushrooms.
Add water and onion soup, sour cream and flour.
Simmer on medium heat.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let cook on low heat for 1 hour. While mixture boils, put into hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate over simmering water in double boiler.
Stir in sugar and 1/2 cup heavy cream.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and no lumps remain.
Beat yolks until smooth. Slowly pour in chocolate mixture while beating yolks constantly. Set aside and cool to room temperature.
When cool, fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into bowls and refrigerate until serving time.
Garnish with a rosette of whipped cream and chocolate curls.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water to a froth.
Mix dry ingredients. Dip pecans in egg white mixture; roll in sugar mixture.
Place on shallow pan and bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Bake Pie shell according to package directions.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: almond toffee bars(almost like candy)
directions: Beat sugar, butter, egg yolk and vanilla together until creamy.
Stir in flour.
Spread in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Break chocolate bar into sections and immediately place on baked layer.
Let set 3 to 5 minutes to melt.
Spread evenly with spatula.
Sprinkle with nuts; lightly press into warm chocolate.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: coke cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Mix butter, shortening, cocoa and coke in saucepan and bring to boil.
Let cool to warm.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk in which soda has been added, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix together and pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: adam knopp's southern fried fish(spicy)
directions: Cut filets into fingerlings or bite size chunks.
Soak in milk for 15 minutes while you mix the corn meal and spices.
Dredge fish into dry mix, coating well and deep fry in vegetable oil. Fry until crispy.
Dip in tartar sauce, lemon or cocktail sauce. Enjoy.

title: cheese and ripe olive spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, and refrigerate for several hours.
Spread on slices of bread and bake at 400° for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: black bean and rice burritos
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Set aside.
Wrap tortillas in foil and place in 200° oven to warm.
Combine beans (with liquid), garlic, tomato, onion, chili powder and cumin in saucepan.
Simmer until tomato begins to soften (about 5 minutes).

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken with onions and 4 cups water.
Remove chicken. Add tomato soup to broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti, garlic salt and pepper.
Cook until spaghetti is done.
Place cut up chicken in casserole.
Whip soup with a spoon and spoon over chicken.
Pour spaghetti over layers and top with cheese.
Bake in medium oven until hot through.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix, chill and form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: roast
directions: Mix together.
Roll roast in mixture and pound into meat (or use fork).
Put remaining in bag with roast and 1 cup water.
Slit top of bag and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/4 of cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix yeast into luke warm water.
Add
oil, salt and sugar; mix in flour, knead and roll out dough.
Sprinkle pizza pans with cornmeal.
Place crusts on pans and sprinkle top of crusts with cornmeal.
Bake crust about 5 minutes at 425°.
Remove the crust from the oven and add filling.

title: grapefruit freeze
directions: Combine sugar and water in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add mint. Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Pour mixture through a wire mesh strainer.
Discard mint. Add grapefruit juice. Divide mixture into two 1-quart containers. Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving. Stir until slushy.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields approximately 2 quarts.

title: asparagus casserole 1
directions: Place asparagus in baking dish.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Cover with cheese and bread crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: smultringer(norwegian munchkin donuts)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add light cream slowly (mixture will separate).
Beat eggs and add to mix.
Add cardamon and vanilla.
Sift flour 3 times with baking powder and salt.
Add to batter and mix well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out on floured cloth into balls.
Heat Crisco and fry 6 at a time until golden brown, turning once or twice. Place on layers of paper towels until cool.
Store in tin with a slice of white bread.

title: quail
directions: Saute veggies in olive oil until onions are clear. Add spices such as sage to taste. Brown quail in olive oil and add to mixture with 1 cup dry white wine and 1/2 cup sherry.
Cook in a 300° oven, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, slowly.
Quail are done when legs and wings separate easily.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in the bag, coating the potatoes well with the cheese mixture.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in a single layer in the pan.
Bake at 375° one hour, turning potatoes after 30 minutes.
When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley.

title: baked stuffed scallops
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except scallops, then toss in scallops and mix well.
Place in greased pie plate and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: a simple treat
directions: Spread one side Ritz with peanut butter.
Mash chocolate drops between fingers and sandwich between 2 crackers.

title: bavarian pot roast
directions: Coat meat with flour.
In large kettle, brown in oil.
Add juice concentrate, onion, bouillon and spices.
Cover and simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes, cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add apples, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: bhatura(indian bread)
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt and ghee together.
Add yogurt and water and knead the dough until it's smooth and soft.
Leave in a warm place 6 to 8 hours (overnight is best).
Break off balls of dough and roll out so that it is thin and about 5-inches wide. Deep fat fry.
As you fry the bread, keep pushing it to the bottom of the pan as it tends to float in the oil.
Bread will puff up and get crispy.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Fry sausage in a pan until done.
Add sausage to rice and stir mixture on low heat for about five minutes.
Serve hot!

title: todd's favorite taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger, add the remaining ingredients.
You can add more or less water depending on desired thickness. Corn, chopped olives and green beans may also be added.
Serve with grated cheese, sour cream and corn chips.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Add refried beans and picante sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cheeses.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: chicken plus
directions: Cover bottom of greased baking dish with dried beef, torn into bite size pieces.
Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon and arrange breasts on dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Refrigerate, covered, 2 hours or overnight. Remove from refrigerator 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake, uncovered for 3 hours at 275° or until tender.
Do not overbake.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Cream the cream cheese with 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well. Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour into 24 paper or foil cupcake cups.
Fill about 1/2 full.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°. Remove from oven.

title: chocolate marshmallow pudding
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water in top of double boiler. Thoroughly mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add to chocolate, stir well until well blended.
Add about 1/4 cup of the milk, stir to a smooth paste.
Stir in the rest of the milk and water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.

When thick, add marshmallows; cover and continue cooking 15 minutes, occasionally stirring. Stir a little of the hot mixture into the beaten egg and return to double boiler for 2 minutes, stirring all the time.
Then remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve warm or cold with milk or cream.

title: pralines
directions: Combine milk, sugar and butter.
Cook until soft ball on candy thermometer.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler. Beat 1 minute with beater to blend.
Place over boiling water and cook, beating constantly, until frosting forms stiff peaks, about 7 minutes (don't overcook).
Remove from boiling water; add vanilla.
Beat to spreading consistency at 2 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Make pudding, using 2 cups milk.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla; beat until pudding thickens.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream, mixing well.
Place layer of graham crackers on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of pudding, another layer of graham crackers, the remaining pudding and top with layer of crackers. Refrigerate.

title: blueberry tea loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, nutmeg and salt; set aside.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add alternately flour mixture with pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips or M&M's.
For each cookie, drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Spread and shape using a spatula.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until firm and lightly browned.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sweet dreams
directions: Preheat broiler.
Spread each cracker with peanut butter.
Top with marshmallows.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil just until marshmallows melt.

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.
Use drained juice for making frosting with confectioners sugar for icing cookies.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour into greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add the hamburger and brown.
Add other ingredients and cook slowly 3 to 4 hours.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper in oleo.
Mix all together, then add cream of mushroom soup.
Pour into 3-quart Pyrex bowl (greased) and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.
Allow 20 minutes to defrost.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel and quarter the apples.
Heat the apples and water to boiling, then reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until apples are tender (5 to 10 minutes).
Stir in the other ingredients.
Make sure the apples are broken or mashed into smaller pieces.
Heat to boiling.
Boil and stir one minute.
Let cool.
Serve topped with cinnamon.

title: zucchini, onion and carrot saute
directions: Tip:
Yellow summer squash may be used for part of the zucchini.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Have butcher butterfly a leg of lamb, or if your able, remove the bone yourself.
Flatten the meat and roast on grill until done to your taste.
It should take about 30 minutes, turning at 5 minute intervals.
Spread with the Herb and Mustard Sauce and slice.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Place pepper halves in boiling salted water.
Reduce heat to a simmer and cook until peppers are tender, about 5 minutes; drain. Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine turkey, bread crumbs, egg, salt, onion and 1 cup of ketchup or tomato sauce.
Stuff peppers with mixture and top with remaining 1 cup ketchup or tomato sauce.
Bake about 1 hour or until sauce is bubbly and meat is cooked through. Makes 6 servings.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add Tabasco sauce.
Pour over cream cheese and serve on crackers.

title: vermicelli soup
directions: Break up vermicelli into small pieces and saute in the fat or oil until a golden brown color.
Then add garlic, onion and tomato puree and cook for five minutes.
Add stock and seasonings and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until vermicelli is tender.
Serves 8.

title: fresh peach bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Gradually add milk; continue beating.
Add vanilla.
Tear bread into large pieces.
Melt butter in cast-iron (or ovenproof) skillet and brown bread until golden.
Remove pan from heat and cool.
Sprinkle sliced peaches with remaining sugar and lemon juice.
Add peaches and bread and pour egg mixture over.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: three minute salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water until dissolved. Let cool. Add fruit. Put half of mixture in oblong dish. Let set until thick. Cover with sour cream and then pour on rest of strawberry mixture. Chill until firm.

title: banana coconut custard
directions: Beat eggs and banana pieces until smooth in a blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour into 6 (8 ounce) custard cups.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg and place in a large baking pan with 1 inch of hot water in it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard has set.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serves 6.

title: baked halibut
directions: Arrange fish in greased shallow baking dish.
Chop green onions, including tops.
Sprinkle over fish.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and basil.
Pour on wine and let marinate 1 hour. Add sour cream.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all together.
Add nuts last.
Pour into sheet pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Boil pie filling and sugar until sugar melts.
Pour into greased pan.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder, shortening and water.
Put on floured surface and roll thin.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut and stretch dumplings and put on top of peach mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: scotty bars
directions: Boil sugar and Karo for 3 minutes; remove from stove and add peanut butter.
Blend with Rice Krispies and spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
In double boiler, combine chocolate and butterscotch bits and melt them.
Pour on top of Rice Krispie mixture and chill until firm.
Cut in squares when icing hardens.
Makes 24 bars.

title: lobster and shrimp salad
directions: Combine shrimp, lobster, celery, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Season to taste.
For each serving, line plate with lettuce.
Put 1/2 cup Chinese noodles in center of lettuce and a serving of salad on top of noodles.
Garnish with tomato wedges, quartered hard-boiled eggs and stuffed celery.
Top with additional mayonnaise and capers.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: chunky chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Stir in cheese, tomatoes and chili powder. Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush crumbs.
Melt margarine.
Mix and pat evenly into dish. Mix eggs, powdered sugar and 1 stick margarine (at room temperature) and beat until fluffy.
Pour and spread over crust; drain pineapple.
Spread on top of mixture.
Slice and add desired amount of bananas on top of pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip. Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix crumbs and milk, let stand for 10 minutes. Add eggs, sugar, melted butter and vanilla. Mix together, then add raisins or coconut. Pour into greased dish, sprinkle with cinnamon mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Trim all fat from chops.
Beat egg white with evaporated skim milk.
Place chops in milk mixture.
Let stand for 5 minutes, turning chops once.
Meanwhile, mix together corn flake crumbs, bread crumbs, hot 'n spicy seasoning and salt.
Remove chops from milk mixture.
Coat thoroughly with crumb mixture.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
Place chops in pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn chops.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings, 186 calories, 4.9 g per serving.

title: decorating frosting
directions: Cream together the Crisco and sugar until well blended, then add the others.

title: cooked soap
directions: Method:
Dissolve the lye in the water and let stand until it is lukewarm.
Add slowly to the fat, stirring constantly until jellylike.
Cook slowly.
Add Borax water and mix thoroughly. Remove from fire; add ammonia and stir until about the consistency of thick honey.
Pour into mold; cut and let cure from 4 to 6 weeks.
Same recipe may be used by omitting Borax or ammonia or either.

title: western hash
directions: In a Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Add onions and green pepper; saut until tender.
Brown ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, pepper and rice.
Cover.
Simmer for 25 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites stiff with sugar.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on foil-covered cookie sheet. Turn off oven.
Put cookies in oven and leave 6 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: incredible fruit dip(cream)
directions: Soften cream cheese and stir in corresponding ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Great with any variety of apples, peaches, strawberries, grapes or bananas.

title: he-man chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients.
Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, buttermilk and oil together.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix soda, salt and flour together; add to first mixture.
Put in muffin tins and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter can be store in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: sweet and sour marinated asparagus
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except asparagus spears and bring to a boil.
Place asparagus spears in a casserole and pour marinade over them.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Drain asparagus and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in a little oil until tender. Drain the corn and lima beans.
Combine the corn, limas, tomato sauce, tomatoes and the cooked onion and pepper with seasonings in an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Lay bacon slices across top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover for the last 10 minutes to crisp bacon.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Wash chilies, remove seeds, lay flat and pat dry.
Mix together grated cheeses.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/2 the chilies, cheese, chilies and cheese.
Mix together eggs, flour and milk. Pour on top of chilies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour on tomato sauce.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute together the sausage and chopped onion and drain very well.
Mix Bisquick, milk and mayonnaise.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sausage mixture on top.

title: spanish delight
directions: In skillet, melt the 4 tablespoons butter.
Add ground beef, chopped onion and crushed garlic; cook until brown.
Drain off fat and set aside.
In saucepan, mix and heat the tomatoes, tomato soup, tomato sauce, mushrooms and olives.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and add the 2 tablespoons margarine, salt and cayenne pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a very large, buttered casserole dish.
Top with 1 pound of grated American cheese.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped popcorn (1 to 1 1/2 cups unpopped) in warm 250° oven so when syrup is ready it is warm or syrup sets up too fast to coat popcorn.
In large heavy pan mix sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook to 230°.
Add peanuts (stir until finished).
Cook to 280°.
Add salt.
Cook to 290°; remove from heat.
Add butter; stir.
It won't all mix in, do fast.
Add soda; stir.
Add vanilla; pour mixture over popcorn.
Stir until coated.
Pour popcorn on countertop or table to cool.
Can make balls or just eat.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown sausage; drain.
Add sauces and simmer. Layer sauce, noodles and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Separate biscuits and place on top of pie.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Separate dough; place in ungreased 9-inch pie pan (casserole dish).
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Drain beef.
Stir in 1 cup Mozzarella cheese (save 1/2 cup for topping), mushrooms, green pepper, ketchup and herbs.
Spoon into crust; top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: dry mushroom soup
directions: Cut mushrooms into small pieces.
Soak mushrooms for 2 hours and wash them.
Cover mushrooms with water in a pot.
Add vegetables and cook until tender; about 1 hour.
Chop onions and fry in oil; add to soup.
Add sauerkraut juice to soup.
Brown flour in oil from onions until nut brown.
Pour 1 cup of soup into browned flour.
Mix well and add to soup.
Bring to boiling point and serve.
Remove stalk of celery and sprigs of parsley before serving.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, milk and egg yolks in medium saucepan over low heat.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Hull, wash and halve berries.
Fill pie shell with berries. In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over medium heat until mix comes to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Slowly stir in jello and stir until jello dissolves. Cool slightly and pour over berries.
Refrigerate and garnish with Cool Whip.

title: brisket
directions: Combine all ingredients (except brisket) and pour over brisket.
Marinate for several hours (overnight).
Cover lightly with foil and bake at 300° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Pour barbecue sauce over brisket; replace foil and bake another hour.

title: candied dill slices
directions: Cook vinegar and sugar over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved.
Place sliced pickles in syrup and cook until boiling. Add celery seed and stir.
Cool, then store in jars in refrigerator until used up.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly and spoon off all fat.
Add the next 7 ingredients.
Stir well.
Heat slowly for 45 to 60 minutes.
The mixture should be thick.
Prepare lasagne noodles according to package instructions, unless you have made your own.
Mix next 5 ingredients into bowl.
Place half of noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half cottage cheese mixture over noodles, half Mozzarella cheese, half meat sauce and repeat layers. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Let lasagne cool for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 10.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Partially freeze steak and slice across the grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery in butter. Remove vegetables, reserving drippings in skillet.
Brown steak in reserved drippings.
Add sauteed vegetables, mushrooms, soy sauce, pepper and 3 tablespoons water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and vegetables, reserving drippings in skillet.
Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water, stirring until cornstarch is dissolved.
Add cornstarch mixture to liquid in skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Return meat and vegetables to skillet.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot bread
directions: Add water to juice of orange to make 1/2 cup.
Drain apricots. Grind raisins and apricots, combine and fold into batter.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Soften cheese in microwave for 15 to 20 seconds on High.
Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar in a bowl until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and peel.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserving several for garnish.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix cake mixes together in large bowl as directed on cake mixes. Add 1 cup chocolate chips and 1 cup coconut. Mix well. Bake as directed on cake mixes. Add nuts if you want.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting. Very rich.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in water and simmer until almost completely cooked.
Remove from broth.
Let cool.
When cool, place in Ziploc bag with bottled barbecue sauce.
Let stand several hours to absorb flavor.
Place on hot grill to finish last few minutes of cooking.
Turn frequently.

title: wonderful pie
directions: Bake pie crusts and cool.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add coconuts and pecans.
Cook on med-low heat until coconut turns brown.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in large serving dish.
Seal top with mayonnaise.
Let set overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: spiced crock-pot beef roast
directions: Place beef in crock-pot.
Combine water with soup mix and remaining ingredients.
Pour over beef.
Cover; cook on low heat setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Remove beef; keep warm.
Pour cooking liquid into a glass measure; skim off fat.
Transfer 3/4 cup of liquid to a freezer container.
Cool slightly.
Seal and freeze up to 6 months.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix soups with 1 can water and set aside.
Mix with hamburger, bread crumbs, eggs, onion, parsley, salt and beef soup mix.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut and brown.
When browned, put into Dutch oven or similar pot with soup mix and cook about 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until creamy.
Add eggs, then flour mix and vanilla.
Chill dough.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet; flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Place pecan nut on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, pumpkin, oil and vanilla; then add remaining ingredients to liquid mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: hot punch
directions: Put cinnamon, cloves and cardamom in basket of percolator and perk liquid mixture.
Makes 15 (6-ounce) servings.

title: skoby's creamed corn
directions: Simmer 20 minutes.
Add butter and crumbs last.

title: cynthia's black eyed pea cornbread
directions: Mix together the corn meal, flour, salt and soda.
Make a well in the center and put in the eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir just until mixed.
Add in the onion, jalapeno pepper, corn and meat and mix again.
Fold in the black eyed peas and cheese.
Pour into well greased pan to at least 1/2 to 3/4 inch thickness.
I like it thicker, so I use a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Test for doneness.
Best when served hot.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Saute carrot and onion in butter until soft.
Add chicken broth, mustard and paprika.
Continue to cook over low heat for about 15 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with milk and add to soup. Remove from heat and cool for about 5 minutes.
Add cheese and beer and return to heat.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve with a sprinkling of parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: glass windows (candy)
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Cool. Mix in nuts and marshmallows.
Put in something that will let it slide out easy.
(I use a Tupperware 12 ounce tumbler).
Put in refrigerator until set.
Run hot water over outside until it slides out.
Roll in coconut.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: tom wopat's a-o-cake
directions: Pour mixture into a greased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and garnish with strawberries if desired.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with pecans.
Sprinkle coconut over pecans.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using eggs, water and oil.
Pour over coconut.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar and margarine. Mixture will be thick.
Spoon and spread evenly over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until cake pulls away from edges of pan.
Cool completely.
Turn over on rectangular cake plate to serve.

title: best baked beans
directions: Drain can of pork and beans.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: candied orange peel
directions: Cut the peel on each orange into quarters then remove the peel in sections. Slice peel in thin strips. Place orange peels in a non aluminum saucepan with enough water to cover the peels. Cover pan and bring to a boil. Cook for 15 min. Drain peels in a colander. Boil water, syrup and 2 c sugar in saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Add peels. Simmer, stirring occasionally, 35 to 55 min, or until peels are translucent and tender. Remove the peels with a slotted spoon to a large rack placed over a baking pan. Let drain and dry about 5 min or till tacky. Place the remaining 3/4 c sugar in a large bowl. Add the peels and coat with sugar. Return sugar coated peels to rack to dry, about 2 hours. Store in an air tight container for up to 1 month. Can also be frozen.

title: lemon icebox dessert
directions: Layer graham crackers in bottom of 8 x 8 baking dish. In a mixing bowl, stir pudding and lemonade powder, then add milk and mix on low speed with hand mixer. Add three-fourths of the fat-free Cool Whip. Pour mixture on graham crackers and top with remaining fat-free Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: garlic roasted new potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Depending on the size of the potatoes, halve or quarter to bite size.
In a shallow roasting pan, toss potatoes with oil, salt, pepper and garlic.
Roast 1 hour or until tender and golden, tossing 2 or 3 times.
Toss with parsley.

title: baked potato-vegetable topped
directions: Spoon cottage cheese over hot potato.
Top with vegetables and dressing.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 1 serving. Preparation time:
10 minutes plus baking potato.
Using nonfat cottage cheese and Kraft Free Italian dressing, contains 370 calories, 2 grams total fat and 15 milligrams cholesterol.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in large pan with next 6 ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender. Remove bones from chicken.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Skim fat. Measure 1/2 cup fat and 2 1/2 cup of broth.
Blend in flour. Stir in broth and milk.
Cook.
Pour all in baking dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake for 20 minutes in 450 degree oven.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and oleo.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Add 7-Up and flavorings alternately with flour.
Bake in a tube pan prepared with grease and flour.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Stick toothpick in cake to check for doneness.
If pick is clean, cake is done.

title: teriyaki meat marinade
directions: Marinate 30 minutes.
Grill or bake meat.
Delicious for chicken.

title: jar "chicken tonight"
directions: Brown chicken in approximately 1 tablespoon of oil; drain. Add Chicken Tonight sauce; cover and simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in 3 round cake pans. Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut together, save 1 cup for topping, and use the rest to place between the cooled cake layers. Combine the reserved coconut mixture with Cool
Whip, and frost sides and top of cake. Refrigerate for three days before serving - or at least try to wait.

title: shoestring potato salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add shoestring potatoes just before serving.
May add tuna or chicken.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to shortening mixture and mix well.
Chill.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries (pit and slice).
Add water to cherry syrup and lemon juice to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Heat but do not boil.
Pour over jello; stir until dissolved.
Chill until partly set.
Add cherries, olives and nuts.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed salisbury steak
directions: Preheat broiler or grill.
Mix beef and soup mix.
Divide into 4 ovals.
Indent with thumb and fill with pepper, cheese and ham. Press meat around and reshape.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn and grill 5 minutes longer for medium rare.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Marinate chicken nuggets in marinade of eggs, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Mix bread crumbs with flour in a big bowl.
Then mix chicken into crumbs until chicken is coated.
Deep fry chicken nuggets in shortening until golden brown on both sides.
Put into deep pan.

title: far east cherries and ham
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple, reserving syrups.
Brown ham in oil.
Combine fruit syrups with brown sugar, cornstarch, mustard, vinegar, soy sauce and pepper.
Add to ham mixture and cook until thickened.
Add green pepper, green onions, cherries and pineapple.
Heat to boiling and cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Serve over steamed rice.
Serves 6.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Blend all the ingredients and form into four individual portions.
Fry on both sides to a brown, about 10 to 12 minutes. Serve with gravy.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir margarine into hot spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form mixture into a "crust" and press into 10-inch pie plate sprayed with nonstick spray.
Spread cottage cheese in bottom of crust.
Cook meat with onion and pepper.
Drain off fat. Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic and heat through.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove bone, chop up and set aside. Reserve broth. Cook spaghetti according to package directions and set aside.
Saute bell pepper, celery and onion in butter and combine with chicken and spaghetti; put in a baking dish.
Pour over enough broth to make mixture very wet.
Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles throughout.
Remove from oven and cover top with cracker crumbs; return to oven to brown or cover top with bread crumbs sprinkled with grated cheese and return to oven until brown.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cut into chunks.
Add sugar and water. Simmer until apples are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add spices and mash with a potato masher.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chewy christmas cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening until they go "plop" when dropped from a spoon.
Add eggs, beaten with vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; add to the creamed mixture, blending well.
(Don't skip sifting.
Some of the nonsifts have a drying effect on cookie doughs where the only moisture is from eggs.)
Grind the dates and raisins and add to mixture, beating well.
(Grinding is important, cutting up the dates and raisins won't do.)
Add pecans and coconut.
It is normal for cookies to fall some after they are out of the oven.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: mexican pie
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper with the ground beef; drain. In cake pan, layer chips (break them up a little so they will lay flat).
On top of chips, beef mixture; on top of ground beef, add the beans; on top of beans, add the Ro-Tel and on top of Ro-Tel, add soup.
Top with any cheese and sprinkle with chili powder. Cook until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Mix well.
Boil 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour into clean, hot jars or freeze.
Makes 2 pints.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix 3 ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Mash with fork. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Makes 4 dozen.

title: pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until comes to a boil.
Stir until foamy.
Add pineapple and freeze in usual way.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add sugar and Dream Whip.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture over the crumb bottom.
Empty 2 cans of blueberry pie filling over this layer.
Spread evenly and top with the rest of the Dream Whip and cream cheese mixture.
You can reserve some of the cracker crumbs for a top garnish, if desired.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place vegetables in bottom of a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch cooking dish.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese, celery and onions; spread over vegetables.
Melt margarine and crumble crackers.
Mix together and spread over top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In a bowl, mix the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables and garlic; stir-fry for 3 minutes, or until tender-crisp.
Remove. Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chicken; stir-fry 4 minutes. Return vegetables.
Stir broth mixture.
Add to skillet, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil; boil 1 minute.
Serves 4.

title: jessie's busy day brownies
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix with electric mixer.
Add one cup walnuts.
Bake exactly 30 minutes in 350° oven in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When I need something in a hurry, this is my favorite and I very seldom have even one to bring home.

title: old-time gravy steak
directions: You will also need a large iron frying pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and coarsely chop apples into a large bowl.
Add sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice together.
Blend shortening and egg into apple mixture.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just until blended.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Press into greased and floured pan (8-inch square); bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool thoroughly on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together for sauce.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake at 375°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly in a large mixing bowl. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add milk and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add confectioners sugar.
Beat with mixer until thick enough to spread.

title: old fashion fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add nuts, jam, flour and milk.
Add other ingredients adding eggs one at a time.
Bake at 350° until done.
Can be baked in loaf pans, Bundt pan or layers.

title: mom's spice cookies
directions: Sift flour onto waxed paper before measuring.
After measuring, resift twice with soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger, and cloves and set aside.
Cream together the butter and shortening, and then gradually add the sugar.
Add egg, orange rind, dark corn syrup and water.
Beat very thoroughly until fluffy light. Gradually stir in the dry ingredients until well blended, and you no longer see flour.
Chill dough about 2 hours after wrapping with plastic.
Cut dough in half and roll out on floured board. Cut with cookie dough cutters.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool.
Shred potatoes.
Add 1/2 cup butter, salt, pepper, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Cover with corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: olive nut sandwich filling
directions: Mash the cream cheese with fork.
Add mayonnaise and blend well.
Stir in pecans, salad olives, olive juice and pepper.
Mix well.
Filling will be slightly mushy, but refrigerate for a few hours and it will firm to spreading consistency.
Serve on bread, toast, lettuce or crackers.
Can refrigerate for 1 to 2 weeks.

title: gloria's snow salmon pie
directions: Note:
You may substitute 2 cans of tuna for all the fish.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Boil berries and vinegar in a saucepan for 3 minutes.
Add sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Pour into shallow container and let set overnight.
Place preserves in jars the next morning, cover with melted paraffin and place lid on jars.
Yields 2 1/2 pints.

title: banana boats(easy)
directions: Peel bananas, save peels.
Cut longways of the banana, a strip out of each banana and save.
Fill hole or tunnel of each banana with chocolate chips and mini marshmallows.
Put top on each banana, the saved piece of banana.
Put peel back on banana.
Wrap each banana with peel with foil.
Place in oven on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° until chocolate marshmallows are melted and hot.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all together and warm up.
Serve hot!
Great for the holidays.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees, with rack in center. Butter two 9x2 inch round cake pans. Line bottoms of the pans with parchment (or wax) paper. Butter paper and dust the pans with flour, tapping out any excess. Set aside. In medium bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside. In mixer bowl, beat oil, vanilla and sugar until combined, about 2 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, incorporating each before adding the next. Beat at medium speed until mixture is pale yellow and fluffy, about 3 minutes. In a medium bowl, mix together bananas, pineapple, walnuts and coconut. Add to egg mixture, stir until well combined. Add flour mixture and blend well. Divide batter between pans. Bake until golden brown and a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean, 30 to 40 minutes. Transfer pans to greased wire rack. Let cool 15 minutes. Run a knife around edges to loosen. Invert onto racks; reinvert, top side up. Cool completely. Assemble cake, or wrap each layer well and freeze. With serrated knife, trim and discard rounded top off one layer. Place layer on serving platter. Using an offset spatula, spread top of layer with 1/4 inch of frosting. Top with untrimmed layer. Frost sides and top with remaining frosting. Decorate with pineapple flowers, if desired. Serve at room temperature (cake can be refrigerated up to 3 days).

title: brownies* * * * *
directions: This soup is basically old family, but somewhere I saw a recipe with the cream cheese, tried it and liked it.
You try it and see what I mean.

title: dirt
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add chocolate pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Grind Oreo cookies in blender.
Layer pudding mixture and ground cookies in a clean flowerpot lined with aluminum foil.
Stick in a few artificial flowers; freeze.
Take out of freezer at least 2 hours before serving.
Makes a delightful centerpiece.

title: mounds drops
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well, then add the next 3 ingredients, making sure to mix well.
Chill several hours. Shape into balls.
Place on waxed paper.
Chill again several hours.
Melt chocolate and wax; dip balls into chocolate.

title: red valentine cake
directions: Cream
butter; add
sugar
and
beat
well.
Add
eggs. Combine next 3
ingredients; add, beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to mixture.
Pour batter into two 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes. Spread on a cream cheese with pecans icing.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Tie first 4 ingredients in a small cloth bag.
Combine spice bag, salt, sugar (if used) and cider in a kettle.
Bring slowly to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove spice bag and serve hot with orange slices (thin) as floaters.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container or can.
Use 2 or 3 tablespoons in an 8-ounce cup of hot water.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Beat in vanilla and egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Blend in milk.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of greased glass that has been dipped into sugar.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 12 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: soap
directions: Mix salt, sugar and peppers well.
Lay ham on piece of brown wrapping paper large enough to wrap ham.
Rub ham with small amounts of mixture until it begins to melt.
Lift ham; cover paper under ham with thin coat of mixture.
Lay it, skin side down, on paper.
Pack remaining mixture on cut side and as much as possible under skin and around the knee joint.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix honey with salt, sugar, oil and oatmeal in large bowl. Add boiling water; when cooled to lukewarm, add yeast and eggs. When yeast is dissolved, add flour and mix.
Leave in bowl, covered with clean towel, for 20 minutes.
Turn onto floured board and knead, adding flour until soft and workable.
Divide into two portions.
Shape and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk. Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes.

title: kathy's special chili
directions: Brown onions, scallions, carrots, celery and mushrooms.
Then add meat and brown.
Add to a large pot.
Add all cans into pot. Add chili mix and chili pepper.
Cook all day or 6 to 8 hours in a crock-pot.

title: lemonade jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water, add lemonade (frozen) and stir until dissolved.
Add 1 3/4 cups cold water.
Refrigerate until thickened, but not solid.
Add Cool Whip and beat with electric mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into an 8-cup mold and chill.
(You can add crushed pineapple if you wish.)

title: cabbage and potato soup
directions: Heat broth.
Add cabbage and potatoes.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 1 cup half and half to broth mixture.
Add onion.
Add remaining half and half and cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with pat of butter, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Cook rice separately.
Mix all together with soups and Velveeta.
Use desired amount of Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Beat egg with Pet Milk and add to flour mixture.
Mix really good. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Pinch off size ball you want to make pie; roll it out and put filling on one half being sure not to get to the edge.
Fold other part over and press together with a fork to seal.
Fry as you get them ready or freeze for later.

title: kyle's baked chicken(serves 6)
directions: Pepper and salt chicken.
Wrap slice of bacon around each chicken breast.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and cheese in blender.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes to brown.
Serve with rice.

title: marinated beans
directions: Drain beans and
chestnuts.
Mix
with	onions in large bowl. Combine vinegar,
sugar, celery seed and oil.
Bring to boil. Pour hot
mixture
over
beans.
Marinate for 24 hours. May be stored for 2 weeks.

title: scalloped potatoes and hamburger
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain.

title: commodore's delight
directions: Put a tablespoon of oil in heavy skillet.
Place over medium heat
and add the beef and cook, tossing and breaking up with a fork, until the beef is lightly browned.
Add onions, green pepper and seasonings and continue cooking until golden brown. Meanwhile, cook the noodles in plenty of boiling water until tender.
Drain thoroughly, then mix with tomato soup, tomatoes and the drained mushrooms.
Grease a 2-quart casserole and arrange half the noodle and beef mixture in bottom.
Top with thin cheese slices.
Add the remaining noodles and beef mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.
Can be made ahead of time, freezes well.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb jello
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in saucepan, bring to a boil.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir and pour into bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: turkey or baked chicken gravy for 50
directions: Let come to a boil (so gravy will be thick), broth, sweet milk, eggs, pepper and salt to taste (if broth not very rich, add small amount of butter), saltine crackers, cooked dressing and gizzards and liver.

title: mountain blueberry cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; cut in shortening until mixture appears like cornmeal.
Then combine eggs and milk. Mix until all is moistened.
Fold in blueberries and pour into two greased cake pans.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: low-fat classic chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl, combine Veg*All, chicken, soup and thyme.
Pour vegetable mixture into greased 2 quart casserole.
In small bowl, combine the biscuit mix and milk with a fork.
Drop a tablespoon at a time over vegetable mixture. Bake uncovered for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown and filling is hot.
Allow pie to cool slightly before serving.

title: easy popovers
directions: Place eggs, milk, flour and salt in mixing bowl; beat 1 1/2 minutes with electric or rotary beater.
Add oil; beat 30 seconds more (don't overbeat).
Fill 6 to 8 well-greased custard cups or muffins tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes; then reduce heat to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until brown and firm.
A few minutes before removing from oven, prick popovers with fork to let steam escape.
If you like popovers dry and crisp, turn oven off, leave popovers in oven 30 minutes with door ajar.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Then add dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13 inch pan.
Bake 350° for 35-40 mins.

title: banana nut bread(margaret's)
directions: Cream sugar and oleo. Add beaten eggs, buttermilk, bananas and vanilla. Stir in flour, salt and soda. Add chopped nuts (pecans). Bake at 250° to 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Test with toothpick. Makes 2 loaves.

title: cinnamon thins
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg
and beat hard.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture and mix.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar with large mixer.
(Keep mixer on entire recipe.)
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well. Add dry ingredients and blend well. Add bananas and mash well.
Pour into two 8-inch loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes (tops of loaves have to be browned).
Goes great with hazelnut coffee!

title: cheddary pasta and vegetables
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, prepare macaroni according to the package direction.
Add carrots, broccoli and pepper for last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients over low heat.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring often.
Add macaroni and vegetables.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown meat.
Salt and pepper it.
Cut carrots and onion up and add Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Pressure cook 45 to 60 minutes at 10 pounds.
Mash well.
Add parsley flakes, 1 bottle chili sauce and the bottle of relish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan except for cheese. Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover for the first 45 minutes.
Add cheese the last five minutes before it's done.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients, except chocolate chips, raisins and nuts, which are optional.
Then fold in the chips, raisins and/or nuts in any combination you choose.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add pumpkin, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, next 5 ingredients and 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: peppermint popcorn balls
directions: Pop popcorn; set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Continue cooking until temperature reaches 270° on a candy thermometer. Add food coloring and peppermint extract.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Stir just enough to mix through syrup.
Slowly stir popcorn in to coat.
Shape into balls with greased hands.
Makes 12 medium.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat water in microwave.
When boiling, add cinnamon hots. Cook until the candy dissolves; stir occasionally.
Take from microwave.
Immediately add jello; stir well.
Cool to lukewarm. Add applesauce.
Refrigerate.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over each layer.
(Can season the ground beef while browning it.)
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° in conventional oven or microwave until potatoes are done.

title: sweet-sour smokies
directions: Combine all ingredients
together,
except hot dogs, in fondue pot.
Mix well and	bring
to a boil.
Add hot dogs and reduce temperature.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over melted butter; do not stir. Combine peaches and remaining 1 cup sugar.
Bring to boil.
While still hot, pour over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until browned.

title: cheese and italian sausage pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick bottom and sides of prepared pie crust with fork.
Bake 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce heat to 350°.
Sprinkle half of sausage over partially baked crust.
Combine remaining ingredients except sausage and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Allow to cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked orange french toast
directions: Spray a large baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Arrange bread in a single layer.
In a medium bowl, whisk together milk, eggs, juice, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour over bread, and turn to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Turn slices again to soak up egg mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake bread 10 minutes.
Turn slices over and bake 10 minutes more. Remove from oven and dust lightly with powdered sugar.
Serve with favorite syrup, jelly or honey.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a large buttered baking dish.
Top with 1 cup or more bread crumbs.
Mix with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Rub 9-inch square pan with margarine.
Melt margarine and chocolate in saucepan.
Remove.
Add all ingredients except eggs. Mix to blend.
Add eggs and beat well.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
Yield: 18 bars.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, pancake syrup and chopped nuts with cinnamon in layer cake pan.
Top with 10 refrigerator biscuits and bake as package directs or until golden brown.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer veggies.
Put mixture of milk and cream of mushroom soup on top.
Spread cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar grapenuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in moderate oven until browned.
Dry and grind before storing in a tight container. Serve cold with milk.

title: chocolate peppermint ice cream cake
directions: Mix Oreo crumbs and margarine.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice ice cream and place on top of Oreo crust.
Spread fudge topping on next, then drizzle with peppermint sauce.
Freeze until firm.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat together until frothy oil and eggs.
Add the sugar and vanilla and blend.
Gradually add the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; blend well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with glaze immediately after removing from oven.

title: potato casserole
directions: Into baking dish add beef, patted down firm.
Place potatoes, soup mixture (soup and water mixed).
Add onions.
Alternate potatoes, beef, onions and soup until gone.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with cheese and return to oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole(no dairy, low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, bring potato, carrot, onion, 1 cup of water and salt to a boil over medium-high heat.
Lower heat to medium, cover and simmer until potato and carrot are tender, about 10 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Blend in nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.
While still hot in pan, pour sauce over, sliding knife around edge to loosen so that sauce will be absorbed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add mushrooms, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper, garlic cheese and soup.
Add broccoli to blended sauce.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus-cauliflower au gratin
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions. Drain.
Combine soup, cheese, milk, mustard and Worcestershire in large saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly until cheese is melted.
Add vegetables.
Mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle around edges of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry pineapple cream
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Toast cornflakes in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix melted butter and sugar; pour over cereal.
Stir until smooth with 3 teaspoons topping.
Mix all other ingredients and stir well.
Freeze 2 hours.
After freezing, mix cheese and spread on top.

title: pineapple yum-yum cake
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; add to this the spaghetti sauce and cottage cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Boil lasagna noodles until tender.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with undrained pineapple.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seeds and pepper in a 1 qt. container with lid. Stir in cucumbers and onions. Cover and chill for 2 hours will keep for 3 days.

title: low cholesterol cake
directions: Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Simmer raisins and water together for at least 5 minutes; drain.
Measure liquid.
Add enough water to bring liquid to 1 1/2 cups.
Add the oil to liquid.
Sift together the sugar, flour, spices and soda; mix well, then add raisins.
Add the liquid and oil mixture, stirring quickly but thoroughly.
If nuts are used, add them last.
Pour into baking pan; bake until cake tests done (usually 30 to 35 minutes).
Powdered sugar may be sprinkled over the top.

title: my own fruitcake
directions: Dissolve baking powder in milk.
Cream sugar and butter together, then add eggs, beating slowly until well blended, then add milk.
Place 1/2 cup flour in fruit mix and toss well.

title: custard
directions: Cook until custard coats a spoon.
Use 1 egg for every cup of milk.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in pie shell (add 1 rounded teaspoonful flour).
Then blend coconut, nuts, brown sugar and 1/3 cup flour.
Lastly, add butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: guinataang rice with corn
directions: Boil washed malagkit rice in coconut milk until half done. Add the corn, sugar and salt.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until rice and corn are cooked.
Add cream, or use it to top each serving.

title: meal-in-one casserole
directions: Fry and season the meat to your taste.
Place cooked meat in a casserole.
Cover with sliced onions and celery.
Add sliced potatoes and rice and tomatoes and enough very hot water to cover all the vegetables.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 350°
oven.

title: mimi's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Add extra juice if dry.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. When done, sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top and put back in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix ingredients in heavy pan.
Bring mixture to a boil, then turn heat to medium.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring all the time.
Take off stove and test in a cup of water.
It should form a soft ball. Add 1/4 pound butter and vanilla.
Beat until ready to pour into buttered dish.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute in a little butter the onion and bell pepper.
Mix in other ingredients and pour in buttered baking dish.
Top with Cheez-Its crumbled and 1 stick margarine melted.
Dribble over top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cheesy spaghetti bake
directions: Brown chuck with onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, 2 1/4 cups water, spaghetti sauce mix, oregano and salt.
Simmer uncovered 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti noodles according to directions, rinse and drain; set aside.
In skillet, melt butter (take away from heat); stir in flour until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup water and milk; stir until smooth.
Put in cheese and place on burner just long enough to melt the cheese and stir until smooth.
