Layer 1/2 spaghetti, 1/2 tomato sauce, cheese sauce (use all of it), remaining spaghetti and remaining tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Can be frozen.

title: chicken salad
directions: Remove chicken from bones.
Discard skin.
Cut chicken finely. Combine chicken with all other ingredients.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Heat peanut oil in a wok or skillet until hot.
Stir-fry squash and carrots about 1 minute.
Add onion and celery for approximately 2 minutes.
Add the rest of the vegetables and stir-fry for another 1 to 2 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and soy sauce and stir-fry approximately 30 seconds.

title: chicken devine
directions: Partially cook broccoli and chicken.
Butter bottom of a casserole dish.
Put broccoli in and then chicken pieces.
Mix remaining mixture together.
Pour the mix over the chicken.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all together and add 1/2 bottle of French dressing.

title: irish rose salad
directions: Cook peas and green beans; set aside to cool. Put a layer of chopped lettuce in the bottom of dish. Add next 6 ingredients. Mix salad dressing and vinegar thinly. Pour over salad. Top with cheese and cauliflower florets dipped in strawberry glaze. Serves 8 to 10.

title: egg rolls
directions: In skillet, place browned hamburger, onions, cabbage, carrots and soy sauce.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Place 2 tablespoons mixture in center of wrap.
Moisten edges with beaten egg.
Roll bottom corner up and sides across and top down.
In hot deep fryer, cook egg rolls until lightly brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: spicy shrimp
directions: Proportions of ingredients are not important; adjust to taste.

title: vegetable bowl
directions: Clean and pare all vegetables.
Cut up and mix.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and oil.
Season with salt and pepper. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Do Not Cover.

title: gumdrop balls
directions: Pour contents of can in top of double boiler.
Add salt; cook until thickened.
Add corn flakes, finely crushed (measure before crushing).
Add gumdrops, nuts and flavoring.
Take out by teaspoonful and roll in coconut.
Let stand on waxed paper until firm.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions.
While cooking noodles, measure soup broth, milk, oleo, salt, pepper and onion flakes in a saucepan and heat until oleo is melted.

title: quick hamburger stew
directions: Saute onion in fat about 5 minutes.
Add meat, cook until lightly brown, stirring frequently.
Add rice and other ingredients.
Cover with tight-fitting lid.
Cook over low heat about 25 minutes or until rice is done.

title: carrot puff
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain.
Mash carrots.
Add margarine, milk, eggs and rest of ingredients.
Mix and pour into lightly greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until set.

title: nestle's congo squares
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the margarine.
Stir in the sugar then remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate chips and nuts, and mix well.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes; cool.
Cut into approximately 35 squares.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break cake up into pieces to fit bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare pudding as directed on box and pour evenly over cake.
Cut strawberries into slices.
Mix well with glaze and spread over pudding.
Spread Cool Whip around outer edges on top of strawberry mixture, letting the strawberries show in middle.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: hot mushroom cheese spread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine ingredients, stirring until blended.
Spread onto bread slices. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Cook squash in water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain and mash.
Add onion, cracker crumbs, eggs, seasonings and half the butter; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: carnival jambalaya
directions: For a quick-to-fix and easy to clean up meal, season to taste one portion per person of lean meat (small steak, pork chop or ground beef patty).
Place each one in the center of individual squares of foil.
Add slice of potato, carrot, onion, peppers or whatever veggies you like and season them to taste.
Close the foil around all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Combine flour, sugar and margarine with fork.
Pat 2/3 mixture into bottom of a 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Sweeten fresh fruit to taste.
Add water 1/2 up the bowl of fruit.
Mash to thicken. Pour thickened fruit into Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle remaining flour mixture on top.
Bake in oven preheated to 375° for approximately 20 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring fruit juices to boil.
Add dissolved gelatin and combine remaining ingredients, except whipped cream and add to gelatin mixture.
Cool until semi-set, then fold in whipped cream.
Pack in 2 quart-size round containers and freeze overnight.

title: zesty pork chops
directions: Pour approximately 2 tablespoons of olive oil in frying pan with heat on medium-high.
Place pork chops in pan; season to taste.
Pour Heinz 57 sauce on each pork chop (1 teaspoon).
When 1st side of pork chops are browned, turn them over, then season that side and cover with Heinz 57 sauce again.
Brown approximately 1 minute.
Lower heat to simmer.
Add 4 ounces water and cover.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add water as needed.
Add mushrooms last 10 minutes.

title: hamburger relish
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop with onions and peppers; add salt.
Let drain 24 hours in a cloth bag.
Then empty into a pan; add sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Heat and put in jars.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour three 9-inch cake pans. Beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.

Cream together the butter and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. In a medium bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, and salt. Stir to mix. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Add the vanilla and mix well.
Fold in the beaten egg whites. Spoon the batter into the three cake pans. Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center one of the layers.
Remove from the pans immediately onto rack for cooling. Must be completely cool before frosting is spread on the layers.

title: people puppy chow(a.k.a. frosty treasures)
directions: Melt butter with chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Blend and pour over cereal. Stir to coat.
Spread on cookie sheet to dry a little.
Put in plastic bag with confectioners sugar and shake lightly until coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: raisin pie
directions: Stew raisins until tender; drain.
Add cream, sugar and flour; cook 5 minutes.
Add the beaten egg yolks.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue; bake in a slow oven.

title: easy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a lightly greased baking dish, layer potatoes, onions, carrots, celery and beef.
Combine the soup, water and seasonings.
Pour over casserole.
Cover; bake for 75 minutes, uncovering for the last 30 minutes so the liquid will thicken.

title: citrus berry sherbet
directions: Soften gelatin in orange and lemon juices.
Add lemon peel and sugar.
Stir over low heat until gelatin and sugar are dissolved; cool.
Stir in strawberries and applesauce.
Pour into a shallow pan and freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Contains 92 calories per serving with about 3 milligrams sodium.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix frozen juices in water and chill.

title: layered summer casserole
directions: Combine bread crumbs, butter and cheese.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half onion, tomato and zucchini; repeat.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Cheddar cheese.
Top with bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk, soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Add enough plain flour to make dough stiff enough to roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° on greased baking sheet.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Bundt pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and pepper; drain.
Add seasoning, tomato sauce and 3 cans water and bring to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes and flour.
Add margarine.
Stir until smooth.
In a baking pan layer tortilla chips, meat mixture and then top with cheese. Repeat layers and bake until cheese melts.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and tortilla chips.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: preschool play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3 quart saucepan and cook until mixture comes away from edge of pan.
Remove from heat.
As soon as it is cool enough to handle, put some baby oil on hands and knead.
Keep in a sealed container.
Lasts several months.

title: crockpot stew
directions: Cook in crockpot for 4 hours or longer.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine margarine, shortening and sugar.

title: tomato and pepper quiche
directions: Sprinkle minced onion over bottoms of pie shells.
Over this put bacon and green pepper.
Arrange tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Whisk until mixed the eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Ladle this over the cheese.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown and fluffy.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all above ingredients and place in 10 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Chop peppers and put in blender with vinegar; add sugar and mix well.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil, 1 minute.
Strain; return to stove and bring to a boil again, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, and at once add Certo and food coloring.
Put into 6 (1/2-pint) jars and seal.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and 1 egg in a large boil.
Stir in flour.
Press dough in bottom and a 1/2 up sides in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake until edges are light brown, 10-15 minutes.
Beat brown sugar, corn syrup, 1 tsp. vanilla and 3 eggs with spoon.
Stir in pecans.

title: german icebox slaw
directions: Cook fusilli or elbow spaghetti according to package directions; drain well.
Cool.
(Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.)

title: tennessee cornbread salad
directions: Crumble half the cornbread into bottom of large serving bowl. In
another
bowl,
combine
tomatoes,
green
peppers, onion, pickles
and
bacon.
Spoon half of mixture over cornbread.
Stir together
mayonnaise
and
pickle juice.
Spread half
the dressing over vegetables.
Repeat layers. Garnish as desired. Cover tightly and chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: philadelphia cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with softened butter until smooth. Add sugar.
Cream the cream cheese, butter and sugar together. Add to mixture eggs alternately with flour, in which 1/2 teaspoon of salt has been sifted.
Add extract and mix all ingredients well.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Boil zucchini for 15 to 20 minutes until soft.
Dish out zucchini from skin.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Mash zucchini with fork and drain. Saute onion in butter until soft. Mix in zucchini, salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle oregano to cover mix.

Add Parmesan cheese to taste (3 to 4 tablespoons). Add approximately 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese and garlic to taste. Stuff shells by layering zucchini and Mozzarella cheese. Bake in a 350° oven until brown on top.

title: sweet cinnamon biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a medium bowl and mix well. Stir in vegetable oil. Add buttermilk and stir just until blended. Knead the dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth. Roll dough into a 15 x 8-inch rectangle.

title: taco lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger. Add chopped onion and taco seasoning. Combine refried beans and cream cheese. Cut tortillas into strips. In a 13 x 9-inch pan layer 1/2 hamburger mixture, then tortilla strips, then 1/2 refried bean mixture, then top with 1 cup each of Pepper Jack and Cheddar cheese. Repeat layers then top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve with sour cream, salsa, shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Sprinkle over dates 1 level teaspoon soda and pour 1/2 cup boiling water over; let stand.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg and cream well.
Mix in 3 cups flour and 1 teaspoon vanilla with the creamed mixture.
Fold in date soda mixture thoroughly.
Last, fold in 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1 cup nuts, if desired. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: hawaiian sweet bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, potato flakes, sugar, salt, ginger, vanilla and yeast.
In medium pan, heat milk, water and margarine until warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid, pineapple juice and eggs to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened, beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
By hand stir in 3 cups flour to form stiff dough.
Knead in 1/2 to 1 cup flour until smooth and elastic (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Place in greased bowl; cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Divide into three parts and form into round balls.
Place in greased 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
Cover and let rise until light and doubled in size (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mold into a ring.
When ready to serve, fill center with strawberry preserves.

title: lemon stichies
directions: Mix
dry
cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg.
Spread in well-greased
pan.
Mix
together
softened
cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Spread over dough mixture and bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.
Quick and delicious!

title: mary lou's venison chili
directions: Trim fat and connective tissue from venison.
Cut into small bite-size pieces.
Heat oil in a large Dutch oven.
Add meat and brown.
Add diced onions and garlic to meat.
Cook until onions are clear.
Add other ingredients and simmer until flavors are well blended, about 1 hour.
If the chili is too thin, let it cook down to the desired consistency.

title: basic tomato sauce
directions: Saute onions in olive oil over medium heat until transparent. Add remaining ingredients (except oregano) and stir.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add oregano and continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Spread evenly over pizza dough.
(Remember to prick the dough first before applying sauce.)

title: chili
directions: Brown meat. Stir in salt and seasonings; add tomatoes, onio ns and greed peppers and water.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: (game) duck gumbo
directions: Cut duck into pieces and brown in oil.
In heavy large iron pot, make a roux; the roux for a duck gumbo should be very dark. When the roux begins to smoke, be very careful as it is about 1 minute from burning.
Immediately add onions, bell peppers and garlic.
Cook down until all vegetables are mushy.
If you have to, add a little water to prevent burning the roux.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Combine first four ingredients in frying pan.
Heat, but do not boil.
Add grated cheese and pimento.
Heat until cheese is spreadable.

title: judy's butterhorn rolls
directions: Heat margarine, Crisco, milk and water in a glass cup in the microwave until melted and hot to the touch. Mix 3 cups of the flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large bowl. Slowly add the hot mixture to the dry mixture. Mix in 3 beaten eggs. Mix in enough more flour (at least one more cup) until thoroughly mixed and becomes a soft dough. Cover dough, let rest 10-15 minutes (leave in the bowl). Divide dough into thirds. Knead about 10 times adding flour, if needed. Roll each third into a 9 inch circle. Brush the circle with melted margarine. Cut into 12 pie shaped pieces. (I use a pizza cutter to cut them). Roll from wide end to point and place on greased cookie sheet, point side down. Brush again with melted margarine. Cover, let raise until very light (20-30 minutes). Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes, or until lightly brown. These freeze very well. Just take out as many as you need and reheat.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Put all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler. Beat with egg beater over boiling water for 7 minutes or until mixture stands up in peaks.
Remove from fire and add vanilla.

title: mom's tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first seven ingredients.
Add flour until soft dough.
Roll out, cut, put on cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.

title: chocolate splinters
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and saltines all over sheet.
Boil sugar and butter until thick. Pour over saltines. Bake 5 minutes at 400°. Remove from oven.
Pour on top the chocolate chips. Spread them all over saltines while warm.
Cover with crushed English walnuts.
Refrigerate and peel off foil. Break up into splinters or squares.

title: oyster crackers munchies
directions: Carefully open inner plastic bag of oyster crackers.
Place crackers in a large bowl.
Mix dressing, oil, dill weed and garlic powder in small bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over crackers.
Return crackers to original plastic bag and box.
Serve.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Add and mix red beans, pork and beans, chili beans and brown beans.
Add brown sugar, catsup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses or Karo syrup, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In saucepan combine pie filling, sugar, pineapple and juice, cornstarch, and food coloring.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Allow to cool.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into pie shells.
Garnish with topping.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and dry thoroughly.
Chop in small pieces including stalks (peel the stalks).
Add raisins, onion and bacon; mix well.
Add sugar.
Blend in mayonnaise and vinegar.
Mix well. Best to make just before serving.
Bacon will become soggy if made too far ahead!

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Spray a 6-cup shallow baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut the cheeses into 1/4-inch cubes.
In a large saucepan of boiling water, cook the macaroni until al dente, 8 to 10 minutes, or according to package directions.
If using fresh broccoli florets, add them to the pasta 3 minutes before the pasta is done.
If using thawed frozen broccoli, pat it dry with a paper towel.
Drain the macaroni (and fresh broccoli) and return it to the saucepan.
Add the cheeses, wheat germ, bacon bits, mustard, salt and ground red pepper.
If using thawed frozen broccoli, add it here.
Spoon the mixture into the prepared baking dish, pour the milk evenly over the top, and bake until bubbly and golden, 18 to 21 minutes.

title: mud cake
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour and soda.
Combine melted margarine, cocoa and boiling water.
Pour over dry sifted ingredients.
Beat quickly and add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Beat again.
Bake in 10 x 15 1/2 cookie sheet pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pilaf
directions: Cook rice, onion and 1/4 cup butter until golden.
Add bouillon.
Cover; cook 20 minutes on simmer.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and a sprinkling of paprika.

title: kris krinkles
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until melted.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix together.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish and let cool.
Mix chocolate chips and butterscotch chips until melted and smooth.
Pour over top lightly and let cool.

title: sex in a pan
directions: Choose a "base".
Mix together and put in a 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or 350° for 15-18 minutes if using brown sugar.
(Best if made the day before.)

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water for about 5 minutes.
Drain. Cook beef and garlic until browned in skillet.
Stir in sauce, salt, oregano and basil into beef mixture.
Stir together the cottage cheese, egg and parsley.
Place half of zucchini in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with half of cottage cheese mixture, half of beef and half of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Save Mozzarella cheese for top.
Bake in a 350° oven to heat through and melt cheese, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: merry cherry chocolate cake
directions: Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth.
Slowly add sugar until smooth and creamy.
Reserve 12 whole cherries and 15 pecan halves.
Chop remaining cherries and pecans.
Combine 3/4 cup cream cheese mixture, 1/4 cup chopped nuts and cherries to make filling.
Place 1 cake layer on plate; top with cherry filling.
Top with remaining layer and ice entire cake.
Press remaining nuts into frosting on side of cake.
Arrange remaining cherries and whole pecans on top as decoration.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Delicious as a salad or dessert.

title: strombolis
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain.
Split the rolls in half lengthwise.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons spaghetti sauce on each roll.
Combine remaining sauce and meat; stir well.
Spread meat mixture on rolls and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts (10 to 15 minutes).
Freezes well.

title: cranberry pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet with shortening. Season with salt, pepper, cloves and nutmeg. Drain excess fat. Combine cranberry sauce, barbecue sauce and 1/4 cup water. Pour over chops. Cover and simmer 1 hour. Remove chops to hot plate and keep warm. Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water. Stir into sauce in skillet. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Spoon over chops. Serve with hot rice.

title: john davis' shrimp macaroni casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add milk, flour, salt, pepper, red pepper and cheese.
Save 1/4 cup for top.

title: veggie medley casserole
directions: Put vegetables in casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup into vegetables, adding a little water if
needed to mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until bubbly and slightly browned at edges.

title: seafood mold
directions: In a saucepan, blend soup, cream cheese and 3 teaspoons of juice from shrimp (discard the rest of the juice).
Add Knox gelatine.
Mix together on low heat.
Then cool and mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Spray mold/pan/dish with Pam and pour in mixture.
Refrigerate.
Prepare the day before serving.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: Toss lightly and chill.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Heat to 120° the honey, oil and water.
Mix all dry ingredients, including yeast, together.
Mix liquid with dry ingredients.
Knead on floured surface for 5 to 10 minutes, until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double. Punch down and form two loaves.
Put in greased bread pans and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crab-swiss bites
directions: Combine crabmeat, green onion, Swiss cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Separate rolls.
Separate each into 3 layers.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and spoon on mixture. Top each with 1 to 2 water chestnut slices.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Makes 36.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit juices in saucepan.
Stir in pudding.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Let cool.
When cooled, pour over fruit, then slice bananas on top and serve.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces into a flat container. Cut up cauliflower and sprinkle over lettuce. Dice onion and sprinkle next. Spread salad dressing over all. Sprinkle sugar next over all, followed by the Parmesan cheese.
Fry bacon crisp and break into small pieces. Sprinkle over the salad.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes an 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Will keep several days refrigerated.

title: nancy's goofy bars
directions: Place dry
cake mix in bowl.
Put eggs in glass measuring cup and add enough water to make 2/3 cup.
Add to cake mix with brown sugar.
Beat
until
blended
and
spread
in a 9 x 13-inch
pan. Sprinkle
with chocolate bits and marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tarheel scratch cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Sift the baking powder and flour together.
Add the salt and mix with the butter, sugar and milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Beat the eggs until stiff and add to the rest of ingredients.
Stir well and bake in buttered layer cake pans for 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
Spread the layers with icing.

title: corn casserole(pennsylvania dutch recipe)
directions: Combine corn, sugar, salt, pepper and egg in baking dish. Add enough milk to cover mixture. Stir in completely. Dot top with butter. Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Recipe can easily be doubled.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir in buttermilk and eggs.
Stir in cracklins. Pour into greased hot pan. Bake 30 minutes in a 450° oven or until brown.

title: deer, onion and potato casserole
directions: Season meat and brown in grease. Peel and slice potatoes thinly. Make alternate layers of meat, potatoes and onions. Pour mushroom soup on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Spread chili sauce on each muffin half.
Sprinkle each with the ingredients in order:
Italian seasoning, Mozzarella, pepperoni and Parmesan.
Place 4 pizzas in microwave at one time on paper towel. Microwave on Medium (60% power) for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Do not overcook or the muffins will get tough.
Do not try to cook all of the pizzas at once because they will not cook evenly.
Makes 8 mini pizzas.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain peaches and apricots. Set juices aside.
Mix peaches and apricots with 1 cup sugar in a large bowl. Set aside.
Melt butter in a baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and remaining ingredients to form a batter.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Pour this mixture over the melted butter.
Do not stir. Put the sugared peaches and apricots on top of the batter.
Bake for 1 hour. This batter will rise to the top to form crust.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put tomatoes in boiling water for 1 minute.
Then put tomatoes in cold water to take off skins.
Cut tomatoes into eighths. Bring tomatoes to a boil and stir to break up.
Add other ingredients; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove cover and boil to reduce liquid.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Dice onion and saute in butter.
Add all other ingredients except for hot dogs.
Put hot dogs in baking dish and pour heated sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, syrup, vanilla and margarine or butter.
Beat with electric mixer until blended. Stir in pecans. Pour mixture into pie shell. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: man pleaser chicken(lo-cal)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken and onions, in a saucepan.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Set aside.
Arrange chicken pieces in shallow open pan, cover chicken with onion slices (do not skimp on the onions) and sauce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well (all ingredients except pecans).
Roll into a ball and coat with chopped pecans.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: meat and potato dish
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Slice potatoes thin in a casserole dish.
Add meat mixture over potatoes; then add the tomatoes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: ground stew
directions: In large skillet, brown ground chuck and drain any fat.
Put in diced potatoes, chopped onions and carrots.
Reduce heat and cover.
Let simmer about an hour, stirring occasionally.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Mix together pineapple juice, dressing mix and seasoned salt. Marinate chicken pieces in sauce 2 to 24 hours.
Drain sauce into saucepan.
Bake chicken, skin side down, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cornstarch and water.
Stir into marinade sauce and bring to boil.
When thickened, turn chicken skin side up and spoon some of the sauce over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes more, adding sauce another time.

title: mocha almond crunch cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a
large mixing bowl.
Beat in egg yolk, coffee, almond and vanilla extracts.
Combine flour and salt. Gradually beat flour into butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Press dough into ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle almonds evenly over dough and pat down gently.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool completely on wire rack. Break into pieces or cut into bars. Easy and tasty.
Yields 35 cookies.

title: fettuccini with asparagus and shrimp
directions: In a bowl, mix shrimp with lemon juice, pepper flakes and salt.
Cook fettuccini according to package directions.
Keep warm in pot.
Heat oil and stir-fry onion, pepper strips and salt until peppers are tender-crisp; remove to bowl.
In same pan, heat oil and add asparagus and shrimp mixture.
Stir-fry until asparagus are tender-crisp and shrimp turn opaque, about 3 minutes.
Stir in pepper mixture and water; heat through.
To serve, toss fettuccini with shrimp mixture and soy sauce.
Sprinkle with grated lemon rind.
Serves 4.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk and rice.
Add drained fruit and nuts.
Chill.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: winter squash souffle
directions: Peel squash; cook until soft in salted boiling water.
Remove and mash.
Mix in salt, pepper, thyme, butter, cream and cheese. Beat in egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into squash. Bake in buttered 2-quart baking dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until set and golden on top.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: 22 minute cake
directions: When cake has been baking for 18 minutes, combine oleo, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add powdered sugar and chopped nuts. Pour over hot cake when removed from oven.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup, milk and mushrooms together.
In glass baking casserole, put bean mixture and 1/2 can of onions; mix. Top with remaining onions.
Cut up butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: asparagus pesto
directions: Steam or microwave asparagus.
Drain well and dry.
In a food processor, pulse pine nuts and garlic with salt until finely chopped.
Add asparagus and oil and pulse until asparagus is coarsely chopped.
Transfer pesto to a bowl and stir in cheese. Serve over penne or other tubular cooked pasta.

title: italian zucchini(appetizer)
directions: Scrub zucchini well.
Cut off ends.
Cook whole in saucepan with salt, consomme, white wine and enough water to make 1-inch liquid in pan.
Cover tightly.
Bring to boiling point.
Boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Vegetables should not be soft.
Watch carefully after 5 minutes of boiling.
Drain.
Chill.
To serve, arrange zucchini in shallow dish.
Mix dressing, scallions and parsley and pour over zucchini.
Place an anchovy on each piece.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with a little of the milk.
Add rest of milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thick.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Add a little of the hot mixture to egg yolks.
Pour back and cook a few minutes longer.
Add the fat and vanilla.
Pour filling into shell.
Cool slightly and cover with meringue.
Bake with meringue on for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: chicken or ham casserole
directions: Layer meat, cheese and onion into a well-greased dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and beat until smooth, using mixer or blender.
Pour over layered foods.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool five minutes before cutting.

title: mother's canned kraut
directions: Chop cabbage as fine as you prefer.
Pack raw cabbage in jars and add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar to each quart. Fill the jars with boiling hot water.
Heat lids and place on jars tightly.
Place canned kraut in a cool dark place and allow it to ferment. Don't worry if some jars bubble and spew (place paper under fermenting jars to protect surface).
Enjoy good kraut.
No cooking or pressuring is necessary for kraut.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a bowl; beat with mixer at medium speed until well blended. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; stir well. Add to sugar mixture; beat just until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour mixture into a 9-inch square baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes; remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate morsels. Let stand 3 minutes or until morsels soften; spread over brownies using a knife. Let cool on a wire rack. Makes 16 brownies.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl beat eggs until foamy. Add flour and sugars.
Beat well.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can be served warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Can also be frozen.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into meat well.
Brown lightly the onion and green pepper; remove from electric skillet.
Brown meat on both sides. Place onion and pepper on meat.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes. Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Add water as needed.
Serve with rice and green salad.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken breast at least 1 hour, but preferably overnight in 3/4 cup of the Italian dressing.
Cook chicken in oven approximately 45 minutes.
Chop coarsely.
Mix chicken with almonds, remaining dressing, mayonnaise, celery, red pepper, green onions, and garlic.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet bread
directions: Dissolve butter, sugar and salt in 1 cup of hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine with other ingredients.
Set this sponge in warm place, free of drafts, overnight.
Cut down in morning and shape into 2 loaves.
Place dough in greased loaf pans and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, then turn out on rack.
Cover with towel while cooling.

title: tiny cinnamon rolls
directions: Unroll dough, and separate into 4 rectangles; pinch seams to seal.
Stir together 1 1/2 tsp sugar and 1/2 tsp cinnamon; sprinkle mixture evenly over rectangles.
Roll up, jellyroll fashion, starting with a long side; press edges to seal.
Cut each log into 5 slices, and place in a lightly greased 8 inch round cake pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Combined powdered sugar, milk, and vanilla, stirring until smooth; drizzle over warm rolls.
Servings: 20 rolls.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut and scrape corn from cob (juicy corn works best).
Add a little water, the fried bacon (crumbled), sugar, salt and pepper (I use lots of pepper) to reserved grease.
Stir in corn.
Bring to a boil and simmer until corn is tender, adding water as needed.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Add 1/4 cup sherry and heat through.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: oreo ice cream pie
directions: Let ice cream slightly soften. Spread 2 c. of ice cream in pie shell; sprinkle with 1 c. cookies crumbs. Repeat with remaining ice cream and cookies crumbs. Freeze for 2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased baking dish. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: super cookie
directions: Press out cookie dough evenly in bottom of an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 18 minutes or until deep golden brown. Cool and decorate as desired. Cut, serve and enjoy!

title: spatzle
directions: Drop by teaspoon into boiling, salted water.
Use small amount of batter on sides of spoon and take out of water when they rise to the top.
Rinse with water and reheat in bowl over low flame.
Can fry with potatoes or eggs or put in soup.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients but chops.
Pour over chops in plastic bag.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: whitey's brats sandwiches
directions: Brown brats; add onions and mangoes.
Cook until tender.
Add sauce.
Simmer until thickened.
Serve on buns.

title: wisconsin holiday fondue
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, brown onion and ground beef. Drain.
Add pizza sauce and seasonings.
Stir until heated.
Add cheese by handfuls.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into fondue pot. Keep warm while serving.
Serve with Italian or French bread. Makes 4 servings.

title: walnut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and oleo in a large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes until oleo is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended. Stir in eggs and vanilla until completely mixed.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 24 brownies.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage and let stand in boiling water.
Melt margarine. Combine 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 1/4 teaspoon garlic salt, 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon, onion and 1/2 or the melted margarine.
Add to meat.
Then add 1 can of tomato paste and rice. Roll 1 tablespoon of mixture in cabbage leaf (secure with toothpick if necessary).
Place in Dutch oven.
Cover with mixture made from remaining can of tomato paste and the salt, pepper, garlic, cinnamon and margarine.
After this is poured over cabbage rolls, cover and steam until cabbage is tender and rice is done (approximately 30 to 45 minutes).

title: easy make ahead "rhubarb gleam"
directions: Wash and cut rhubarb in 1-inch pieces.
Cover with water and boil until rhubarb is tender.
Add sugar immediately and cool.

title: pumpkin, date, nut, raisin bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture, then pumpkin.
If pumpkin is too thick, you may need to add water.
Stir in dates, nuts and raisins.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
It's really better to line the bottom of the pans with waxed paper.
Bake one hour or until done at 350°.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Mix together the orange jello, tapioca pudding and water; refrigerate overnight.
Next day, beat mixture for 7 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip and drained mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate; serve when ready.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Mix the next 3 ingredients together. Now, combine all 7 ingredients together. Better if refrigerated 2 hours before serving.

title: marinated cucumbers & onions
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, and pepper.
Add additional water if vinegar taste to strong.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Place in fridge.
Prepare enough ahead of time to flavor cucumbers, but not so far ahead that cucumber wilt.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together.
Put 3 to 4 large spoonfuls of mixture in large cup and add boiling water.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Beat 2 eggs at a time.
Beat in 4 cups flour.
Add whiskey at end and beat in well.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured angel food pan for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours depending on oven.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour,	oats
and
1/2 cup brown sugar with 1/2 cup margarine.	Blend
with
electric mixer at low speed until crumbly.
Press
into
ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for
15 to 20 minutes.
Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar,
salt and spices in mixing bowl.
Pour over baked bottom and	bake 20 minutes more.
Combine pecans, brown sugar and margarine.	Sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.	Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peas in basil butter
directions: Cook snow peas 5 minutes until crisp and tender, per package. Beat butter in small bowl with basil, orange rind and a little pepper.
Mix until well blended.
Drain peas.
Add sauce to peas.

title: macaroni and vegetable casserole
directions: Cook elbow macaroni in boiling water for 8 minutes; drain. Cut Spam into bite size pieces; place in bowl.
Season with the teriyaki sauce, mixed with the Worcestershire sauce.
Allow this to soak for a few minutes.
Sear meat in frypan for 5 minutes, or until browned.
Place macaroni in 3-quart casserole oven dish. Add the Italian style stewed tomatoes and the milk.
Chop the frozen vegetables into bite size pieces; mix thoroughly with macaroni and tomatoes.
Bake in the oven at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Measure Bisquick into large bowl.
Cut in the softened margarine (texture should be fine grained before adding other ingredients).
Blend in sour cream.
Fold in cheese.
Mixture will be stiff.
Use hands to mix.
Fill mini muffin pans (sprayed with Pam) 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 3 dozen mini muffins.

title: aunt leona's pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and milk in large bowl.
Add shortening, then add flour mixture all at once.
Beat until smooth.
Get griddle hot, or test it with a little batter.
When the top is full of air bubbles, turn only once.
They are as light as a feather.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Fold in bread.
Bake in 3 quart casserole at 400° until browned, 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces; cover with water and cook for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Make a white sauce from the butter, flour, salt and pepper and milk.
Stir constantly until thickened.
In 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish, layer the cabbage, sauce and cheese. Repeat twice.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops in sour cream
directions: Crushed dried sage.
Mix with salt and a dash of pepper. Brown lightly on both sides in hot shortening.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onions; dissolve bouillon cube in 1/4 cup boiling water. Pour over chops.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until meat is done.
Place meat on serving platter.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix together cake mix,
1 stick oleo and 2 eggs.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Do not bake just yet.
In another bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour this mixture over the German chocolate cake mixture in pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cake cool completely.
Cut into bars next day.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Cook ground beef in a little vegetable oil until browned. Drain off excess fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and mushrooms to meat; mix well.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: roast beef
directions: Wash both sides of meat and sprinkle with garlic powder. Place in Corning Ware dish or appropriate sized pan.
Add both soups and both cans water.
Cover and roast at 325° for 3 hours or until meat falls apart with a fork.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook fryer; bone and cut in small pieces.
Melt butter and pour over dressing mix; set aside.
Mix 1 cup chicken broth with cream of mushroom soup.
Mix 1 cup chicken broth with cream of chicken soup.
Put aside 1 cup of the dressing mix.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Cream first four ingredients in blender.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: microwave oven no-fail divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave oven 20 minutes or until candy thermometer reads 260°.
Stir every 5 minutes during cooking time.

title: carrot - coleslaw salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add cold water, vinegar, salad dressing, salt and pepper and stir until blended.
Chill until partially set.
Beat chilled mixture; add carrots, green pepper, onion, relish and cabbage.
Chill until firm.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ham delights
directions: Saute onion, margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire and mustard.
Slice rolls; layer ham and cheese on rolls that have been spread with sauteed mixture; bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine first six ingredients in saucepan and stir well. Place over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add nuts, stirring until well coated.
Spread nuts on waxed paper and separate with a fork.

title: blackberry pinwheel cobbler
directions: Boil until thick.
Pour over hot rolls.

title: apple-sweet sweet potatoes
directions: Cook whole sweet potatoes in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Peel and slice lengthwise about 1/2-inch thick.
Layer slices in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with apple slices.
In a saucepan, bring the 1 cup of apple juice to boil.
Dissolve the cornstarch in the 3 tablespoons of apple juice and add to the hot apple juice.
Stir until thickened.
Stir in honey.
Pour the sauce over the apples and sweet potatoes.
Combine the wheat germ and graham cracker crumbs; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender when checked with fork. Makes 8 servings.
One serving is 168 calories and 1 gram of fat.

title: bishop sheen's meat loaf
directions: Put meat in bowl.
Add onions, bread, green peppers, garlic, applesauce, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add egg and mix well.
Form into loaf and flour well.
Oil pan and place loaf in pan.
Add catsup on top of loaf.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours, uncovering for the last 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine egg, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder together.
Add to zucchini; mix well.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Grease and flour 2 bread loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
